To test coincident moving loop EM and resistivity target (R1).

HoleGeneralComment: Drill hole abandoned in overburden due to technical difficulties.

HolePurposeComment: Test moving loop pick at 2+00S with angle ddh in area of potential u/c offset
HoleGeneralComment: Drill hole intersected background sandstone column with graphite well below expected target.  Basement downhole radiometric peak of 856 cps in silicified zone above graphitic unit.

HolePurposeComment: To test for basement offset and strike extension of conductor intersected in fence 122-126-140 located 200 m to the west.
HoleGeneralComment: Drill hole intersected several structural zones in the sandstone. Strong bleaching in the lower 20 m with some grey clay. Strongly graphitic basement with cordierite augen zones.  Small zones of reactivation in the basement.

HolePurposeComment: To evaluate the conductor intersected in ddh WC-241 100 m along strike to the west.
HoleGeneralComment: Drill hole intersected structured upper sandstone but with limited structure in lower sandstone.  Moderate to strong bleaching immediate basal sandstone.  Strong graphite and pyrite within cordierite pelitic gneiss - local large cordierite augens.

HolePurposeComment: Fence north of WC-242 to evaluate the anomalous sandstone geochemistry and to determine the thickness of the basement cordierite augen gneiss conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected regional sandstone with minor alteration and structures above the unconformity.  The drillhole intersected strongly graphitic cordierite-bearing metasediments with a transition to graphitic metasediments towards the end of the hole.

HolePurposeComment: Fence south of WC-242 to evaluate the anomalous sandstone geochemistry to determine the thickness of the basement cordierite augen gneiss and to possibly evaluate the basement geology directly east of the orebody.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected high-grade mineralisation at the unconformity anomalous alteration above the mineralisation and numerous remobilised graphitic structures in the basement.

HolePurposeComment: Fence south of WC-241 and 100 meters east of WC-244 to test the potential eastern extension of mineralisation encountered in WC-244.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected anomalous alteration structures and quartz removal in the basal sandstone and a narrow mineralised interval at the unconformity.

HolePurposeComment: To test the possible extension of mineralisation 100 meters west of WC-244.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected regional sandstone with some weakly anomalous alteration in the basal sandstone.  The drillhole intersected cordierite-graphite-pyrite metapelites with little structure evident.

HolePurposeComment: To test approximately 25 meters south of the mineralised intersection in WC-245.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected anomalous alteration and structures throughout a majority of the sandstone.  The basement comprises graphitic cordierite bearing metasediments with localised structures.

HolePurposeComment: To evaluate the basement stratigraphy potential structural offsets and unconformity changes between WC-240A and WC-241.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected some anomalous alteration and weakly structured basal sandstone.  The basement comprises weakly structured graphitic-pyritic cordierite bearing metasediments.

HolePurposeComment: To evaluate the metamorphic stratigraphy on the Tibia project with an angled and oriented drillhole.  This drillhole is also designed to test possible extensions to mineralisation southeast of CIG-184.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected strongly brecciated and altered basal sandstone.  The basement is dominated by fine-grained weakly graphitic metapelite and pegmatite with a zone of brittle-ductile cataclasite towards the end of the hole.

HolePurposeComment: Deep piezometer drillhole.  Drilled by Cameco.
HoleGeneralComment: Drilled this hole on the PAD" with the intent of installing a piezometer grouted the rods in could not install the piezometer had to do a redrill "CL-07-256"; "BARREN" MDH completed a geotech. and litho log."

HolePurposeComment: Deep piezometer drillhole.  Drilled by Cameco.
HoleGeneralComment: Drilled this hole on the PAD" inflow area successfully installed the Piezometers; "BARREN" MDH completed a geotech and litho log."

HoleGeneralComment: Regional piezometer hole drilled on the road going down to the boat launch successfully installed the piezometers; BARREN" MDH completed a geotech and litho log."

HoleGeneralComment: Regional piezometer hole drilled up at the Sask. Tower hill successfully installed the  piezometers; BARREN"  MDH completed a geotech and litho log."

HolePurposeComment: Deep piezometer drillhole.  Drilled by Cameco.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional piezometer hole drilled by the MWT plant" successfully installed the piezometers; "BARREN"  MDH completed a geotechnical and lithological log."

HolePurposeComment: Deep piezometer drillhole.  Drilled by Cameco.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional piezometer hole drilled on the north side of the road across from the stockpiles successfully installed the piezometers; BARREN" MDH completed a geotech and litholo log."

HolePurposeComment: Deep piezometer drillhole.  Drilled by Cameco.
HoleGeneralComment: This hole was the replacement hole for CL-07-250 drilled on the PAD" area in the inflow area successfully installed the piezometer; "BARREN" MDH completed a geotech and litholo log."

HolePurposeComment: To fence 20m north of WC-244 mineralization to confirm potential across-strike width.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected altered and faulted basal sandstone with zones of elevated radioactivity over 100m above the unconformity.  Weak to moderate mineralization was encountered above and immediately below the unconformity.

HolePurposeComment: To fence 20 m south of WC-244 mineralization to confirm potential across-strike width.
HoleGeneralComment: Rods became stuck at 141 m (possibly due to sanding in at the bottom of the casing).  Attempts were made to free the rods however the hole was abandoned and the redrill hole (WC-258A) was commenced.

HolePurposeComment: To fence 20m south of WC-244 mineralization to confirm potential across-strike width.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected altered and faulted basal sandstone with zones of pervasive clay replacement immediately above and below the unconformity.  Significantly elevated radioactivity or mineralization was not intersected.  The upper basement has undergone significant bleaching argillization and dissolution.

HolePurposeComment: To fence 20m north of WC-245 mineralization to test for the presence of a mineralized pod along-strike from the WC-244 mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected mild to moderately altered basal sandstone before entering a zone of strong chlorite alteration with patchy dissolution and then a wide zone of strongly altered and mineralized sandstone.  Mineralization continued until the unconformity.  The upper basement is moderately to strongly altered and bleached.  Cordierite-graphite-pyrite Metapelitic Gneiss was intersected throughout the drilled basement.

HolePurposeComment: To infill between WC-244 and WC-259 fences and target the mineralized horizon encountered in these drillholes.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected moderately altered and friable basal sandstone then entered a zone of strong alteration and low to medium-grade mineralization within clay-chlorite rock.   Narrow zones of perched mineralization are present up to 130m above the unconformity.  The upper basement is strongly altered and bleached cordierite-graphite-pyrite Metapelitic Gneiss.  Ductile deformation persists for most of the drilled basement.

HolePurposeComment: To fence 50m north of WC-248 to test the possibility that WC-248 was under-drilled and to determine further along strike potential of Cigar East mineralized pod.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected largely unstructured mild to moderately bleached sandstone.  The basal sandstone is chlorite altered and contains pyrite veining.  No mineralization was intersected.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 50m to the west of the WC-244 mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected moderately to strongly bleached and altered basal sandstone.  A narrow zone of low grade mineralization was intersected above the unconformity.  The upper basement is strongly altered before progressing to unaltered fine grained Metapelite and cordierite-graphite-pyrite Metapelitic Gneiss until the end of the hole.

HolePurposeComment: To test a zone of illite altered basal sandstone south of WC-246.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected regional sandstone with zones of patchy bleaching and weakly developed fractures/jointing. A narrow basement wedge is present above the unconformity with associated strong alteration. The basement lithologies are graphitic and probably analogous with the prospective basement corridor. Brittle-ductile shear zones have been developed over various locations within the intersected basement.

HolePurposeComment: To infill between WC-259 and WC-261.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected moderately to strongly bleached somewhat dirty sandstone.  Fracture density and faulting increases with depth.  The basal sandstone is strongly altered and contains veined and disseminated pyrite and siderite.  Significant mineralization was not intersected.  The intersected basement is the prospective cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss and quartz dissolution and alteration is present beneath the unconformity.

HolePurposeComment: To fence grid-south of section 5 (historical drillholes CIG-178A and CIG-180).
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected highly anomalous upper sandstone; strong bleaching and fracture/fault development. The lower sandstone was more regional in appearance. The basement is composed of cataclasite and brittle-ductile structures overprinting psammopelitic gneiss; calc-silicates and pegmatite.

HolePurposeComment: To fence grid-north of section 3 (historical drillholes CIG-171 and CIG-163).
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected moderately to strongly bleached sandstone with zones of faulting and elevated fracture density. The basal sandstone is moderately to strongly altered and faulted with above background radiometry. Narrow zones of low grade mineralization were intersected. The basement is a mixture of weakly graphitic psammopelitic gneiss and calc-silicates with regular zones of brittle-ductile shearing and narrow cataclasite development.

HolePurposeComment: To fence grid-north of section 4 (historical drillholes CIG-174A; 172; 176 & 184).
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected poorly fractured yet moderately to strongly bleached sandstone. The basal sandstone intersected a zone of moderate secondary hematite and clay alteration with elevated radiometry.  The basement is strongly brittle-ductile deformed with abundant cataclasite development.

To intercept the unconformity approximately 25 m north of WC-264 and test the continuity of mineralization east of WC-259.  Also designed to test the possibility of major north-trending structures.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected moderately bleached sandstone throughout much of the sandstone with primary hematite persisting throughout much of the MFb.  Moderate grade mineralization was intersected at the unconformity with abundant Ni-arsenides.  The basement is composed of cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: To fence approximately 100 m south of WC-240A.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected bleached and faulted MFc.  The MFb was regional in appearance and structure and the basement lithologies were dominated by felsic gneiss; biotite psammopelitic gneiss and pegmatite.

HolePurposeComment: To fence approximately 90 m south of WC-288.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected regional upper sandstone with strongly fractured and bleached lower sandstone.  Closer to the unconformity the sandstone displayed numerous zones of pervasive clay alteration and core loss.  Weak uranium mineralization was intersected at the unconformity.  The upper basement was comprised of cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss; argillised and quartz dissolution was prevalent throughout.  The lower basement consisted of graphite-sulphide poor psammopelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: To fence approximately 60 m west of WC-244.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected bleached upper sandstone and bleached basal sandstone with a protected core of primary hematite sandstone in the upper MFb.  This zone of hematite sandstone displayed elevated radiometry.  The sandstone above the unconformity is altered and contains elevated radiometry.  The basement intersected predominantly cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss with narrow intervals of fine-grained metapelitic gneiss.  Argillisation and graphite-remobilized fault gouges are limited to the upper basement.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 100 m west of the WC-246 and WC-263 fence.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected moderately bleached upper sandstone. Poorly bleached and moderately to strongly primary hematite banded lower sandstone.  The sandstone overall is poorly structured.  Elevated radiometry was intersected at the unconformity and weakly elevated radiometry was intersected in the upper MFb.  The intersected basement was comprised of cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: Shaft #2 Geotechnical; to target structure 8 m updip of CL285; cored to 164 m then hole sanded in and was abandoned.
To drill approximately 100 m south of WC-291.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole was abandoned due to incorrect casing installation.  Rods became stuck at 63 m.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 100 m south of WC-291.  Redrill of WC-293.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole was abandoned - NW casing broke during installation.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 100 m south of WC-291.  Redrill of WC-293A.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected bleached and poorly structured sandstone.  Some structures throughout the sandstone displayed sulphide coatings.  The basal sandstone is argillised and faulted; only minor elevated radiometry is associated with the basal sandstone.  The intersected basement is dominated by graphitic metapelitic gneiss; the lower basement is cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss; porphyroblastic in part.

HolePurposeComment: Shaft #2 Geotechnical; to target structure southwest of Shaft #2 and updip 10 m from where structure intersected CL285; hole abandoned @ 461 m due to coarse sand infill.
To drill approximately 100 m east of historical line 12+50E (DG1 grid)
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected moderately bleached and poorly structured sandstone.  Structures become more developed with depth with common faulting and pervasive clay replacement developed in the basal sandstone.  Elevated radiometry is present above the unconformity.  The basement lithologies are dominated by gr-py-(cd) metapelitic gneiss and are only weakly structured.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 40 m south of WC-295.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected strongly to moderately bleached poorly to moderately structured sandstone.  The basal sandstone is moderately structured with local drusy quartz coated fracture planes. The basal sandstone also contains slightly elevated radiometry.  The basement consists of dominantly Graphite Pyrite Cordierite fine to coarse grained Metapelitic Gneiss;  with a relatively strongly developed paleoweathering profile.  Basement is poorly structured with local moderately fractured graphite coated structural zones.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 25 m south of WC-289.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected strongly to moderatley bleached; poorly fractured sandstone with rare structural zones with local rubbly core and enhanced friability and local zones of strong drusy quartz healed fractures within the basal section of the sandstone.  Minor elevated radiometry in the basal sandstone.  The basement section was is composed of dominantly fine and coarse grained Graphitic Cordierite Pyrite Metapelitic Gneiss.  Basement is poorly fractured with rare structural zones.

HolePurposeComment: The first hole on a new fence between the Tibia and Tibia East areas.  Designed to test the down-dip extension of a structural corridor intersected in the upper sandstone of WC-265.
HoleGeneralComment: The drillhole intersected strongly bleached sandstone.  Silica flooded healed structures are common throughout the sandstone.  The basal sandstone is strongly structured with common fault brecciation and associated alteration.  Elevated radiometry is present throughout much of the basal sandstone.  The basement is dominated by psammopelitic gneiss; possibly cd-bearing in places.  Weak cataclasite development but overall poorly structured.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 40 m southeast of WC-298.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderate to strong bleaching of sandstone up to 250 m with weak to moderate below. Silicified between 296-358 m. Mostly poorly structured sandstone with narrow fracture zones. The basement is dominated by graphite pyrite +/- cordierite pelitic to psammo pelitic gneiss. Weak to strong brittle/ductile deformation throughout the basement. Short intervals of cataclasite/breccia.

HolePurposeComment: To drill approximately 100 m northeast of WC-299.
HoleGeneralComment: The sandstone was moderately to strongly bleached up to 260 m with weak to moderate bleaching below. Local traces of pyrite along fracture planes. Minor blocky/fractured intervals below 169 m. Strongly structured sandstone between 307-403 m with local weak to moderate silicification. The basement geology is dominated by graphite pyrite +/- cordierite pelitic to psammo pelitic gneiss with pegmatite sections. Local zones with weak to locally moderate brittle/ductile deformation.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 50 m north of CIG-181.
HoleGeneralComment: The hole intersected moderately to strongly bleached yet competent MFc.  The upper MFb is strongly bleached but trends into a poorly bleached regional sandstone.  Closer to the unconformity the sandstone becomes strongly altered with abundant core loss and weakly elevated radiometry.  The upper basement is strongly bleached and argillised; the majority of the basement is cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 50 m south of CIG-181.
HoleGeneralComment: The hole intersected structured and altered MFc - numerous near vertical fractures and faults; some with clay and pyrite coatings.  The lower MFc and upper MFb are poorly structured and moderately bleached.  The basal sandstone becomes fractured and strongly altered above the unconformity.  The basement is comprised of dominant cd-gr-py metapelitic gneiss and fine-grained metapelitic gneiss.  Poorly structured and altered throughout.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 50 m south of WC-296.
HoleGeneralComment: The hole intersected moderately to strongly bleached; poorly structured MFc. The MFb is moderately to strongly bleached with local structure zones associated with abundant drusy quartz & minor argillization. From 454.2 m the basal sandstone is highly altered with pervasive clay replacement; local limonite staining; local hydrothermal hematite alteration & patchy low-grade mineralization. The basement is dominated by inequigranular cd(<5 mm)-gr-py metapelitic gneiss with narrow fine grained gr-py metapelitic gneiss. Narrow local increased brittle/ductile deformation intervals & variable anatectic sweats throughout. The basement becomes  fresh from 539.4m.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 50 m south of WC-293B.
HoleGeneralComment: The hole intersected str bleached upper MFc and wk bleached; mod hematized; poorly struct with local structural zones in the lower MFc. The upper MFb was wk-mod bleached and locally struct; the basal sst was str bleached and mod structwith narrow intervals of pervasive clay replacement. Brecciated NiAs and strongly chloritization from 457.9-458.2 m str chloritization continuing  to the u/c at 459 m. The bsmt intersected wk bleached upper basement with low grade mineralization along a fracture at 461.1 m. Bsmt lithology consisted of cord-pyr-graph mp gneiss. Cord were variably sized <5 mm; 5-10 mm and >10 mm. Graphitic units >10% were also present. The basement becomes fresh from 549.2m.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 50 m north of WC-295.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc was weakly to moderately bleached and poorly structured; the lower MFc and upper MFb were moderately silicified with perserved diagenetic hematite. The MFb was poorly structured with moderate drusy quartz along fracture planes in the basal 20 m; the basal sandstone become moderately to locally strongly bleached from 444 m. The basement intersected a thin (<1 m) red/green paleoweathering zone and strongly chloritized interval with quartz dissolution from 461.35-463.4 m. The basement lithology is dominately cordierite (<5 mm)-pyrite-graphitic metapelitic gneiss with porphyroblastic cordierite intervals.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 100 m south of WC-258A.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc was moderately bleached and poorly structured with local narrow moderately structured intervals; the upper MFb was moderately to strongly hematized and poorly structured; the basal sandstone was weakly to modeartely bleached and poorly structured with rare local moderately structured intervals. The unconformity at 455.36m was followed by a 10m paleoweathering profile. The basement intersection was dominantly cord-gr-pyr metapelitic gneiss with common anatectic sweats and pegmatite stringers; from 472.5-495.6m trace argillized zone with a moderately argillized interval and ghost cordierites? Increasingly fresh basement from 538m with trace chloritization and fresh biotite.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 50 m east of WC-289.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper MFc was strongly to locally moderately bleached and relatively unstructured.  The lower sandstone of the MFb was overall weakly to locally strongly bleached with the basal sequence from 411.1 m to the unconformity being intensely structured and altered with abundant core loss; increased fracturation and faulting; rotated bedding and pervasive argillization.  No mineralization was intersected at the unconformity.  The basement was composed of entirely unaltered calcsilicate/quartzofeldspathic gneiss; displaying a well developed paleoweathering profile.

HolePurposeComment: To target the unconformity approximately 50m south of WC-307.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper sst was pervasively bleached but poorly structured with poor fracturation and weak faulting encountered at 81.2 m depth.  The lower sst was poorly bleached; unaltered and relatively unstructured with moderate bleaching local pyrite and weak quartz dissolution noted within the basal conglomeratic sequence.  The u/c was sharp and unaltered with a thin mod chloritized paleoweathering profile extending 3 m below the u/c.  The bsmt intersection was composed of mod altered locally str bleached and structured graph/cord bearing metapelitic gneiss.  A gradational contact between the prospective metapelitic sequence and a quartzofeldspathic unit was encountered at 534.8 m depth.

HolePurposeComment: To target the unconformity approximately 40 m ENE of WC-308.  Targeting the region along strike from the anomalous basal sandstone package intersected in WC-307 and the anomalous upper basement sequence in WC-308.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper MFc member was strongly bleached but unstructured and unaltered.  The MFb however was overall poorly bleached and fractured with moderate bleached sandstone intersected at 374.6m drilled depth.  The basal sandstone was very strongly bleached but poorly structured with very local increased fracturation noted proximal to the unconformity.  The unconformity was sharp and unaltered with a thin weakly bleached zone.  The entire bsmt intersection was poorly altered with a well developed extensive paleoweathering profile. The bsmt comprised of locally graphitic metapelitic gneiss down to 435.4m depth; with the remainder of the bsmt intersection being composed of poorly structured and altered quartzofeldspathic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 50 m south of WC-309.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc was pervasively bleached; overall unstructured; local str argillized broken up flt zone from 95.1-98.4 m. MFb was intersected at 170.7 m with the unit being poorly bleached; unaltered with wk patchy silicif  down to 260 m. Mod bleached sst was intersected ~ 30m above the u/c with basal sst/conglomeratic unit being very poorly bleached; unaltered with common heavy mineral bands. The bsmt intersection was composed entirely of wk-mod graph cord mp gn.  The bsmt was poorly altered with a well developed extensive paleoweathering profile consisting of a thick bleached zone; red zone & green zone which extended to 444.8 m.  Bsmt was overall poorly structured with very local thin graph struc. zones.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 190 m south of WC-297.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper sst was strongly bleached and weakly structured becoming moderately structured near the base of the MFc. The MFb was wk-mod structured with strongly structured zones at 230.4-244.4 m and 334.55-347.9 m and 432-442.8 m. Abundant fault gouges; fault breccias; narrow strongly silicified intervals; completely rubbly core and associated friability and argillization within structured zones. A narrow pwp profile following the unconformity at 452.3 m. The bsmt intersection consists of cord-pyr-graph mp gneiss; with several units being graphitic (>10 %). Evidence of weak ductile deformation in the upper basement from 461.7-472.8 with associated trace to weak argillization. Overall the basement was poorly structured.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 200 m west-southwest of WC-239.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc is poorly structured and wk-mod bleached. Common liesegang bands and points rouge. The upper MFb continues to be poorly bleached with mod-str hematite staining. Poorly structured. Weak silicification in places and associated druzy quartz fracture coatings. The lower MFb becomes mod-str bleached with depth.  Increased structure including faulting and associated argillisation is present closer to the unconformity. The upper basement (altered metapelitic gneiss) is argillised and weakly bleached overprinting a narrow pwp profile. Common graphitic fault gouges and sulphide veining. The basement overall is a graphitic metapelite with common to abundant cordierite. The lower bsmt is anatectised and poorly structured.

HolePurposeComment: To test the unconformity approximately 70 m south-southwest of WC-312.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper MFc consisted of strongly surficially bleached sandstone. The remainder of the MFc and MFb was moderately to strongly hematized; unaltered; poorly structured sandstone. The basal MFb had common heavy mineral laminations parallel to bedding. A narrow 10 cm argillized interval at the unconformity @ 375.9 m. The basement intersected a complete paleoweathering profile 37 m thick followed by dominantly biotite quartzo-feldspathic gneiss; with narrow qtz-feld-bio pegmatites and a biotite-bearing quartzite.The basal intersection consisted of phlogopite quartzo-feldspathic gneiss. Overall the basement was unaltered; poorly structured and moderately to well foliated.

HolePurposeComment: To target the regional foliation along strike from CIG-83 and commence the last remaining fence between Tibia and Tibia East.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc and upper MFb was mod- str bleached; poorly struct with patchy tr lim staining throughout the upper 170 m. The remaining sst column down to 380 m consisted of tr-wk bleaching; poorly struct sst. The basal sst was mod bleached with a scattered yellow coloration consistent with local regional looking sst; overall poorly structured. The basal 4 m above the mineralized zone was grey colored. The mineralized intersection consisted of dark grey/black generally competent sst. A sharp u/c contact at 425.45 m followed by a narrow overprinted PWP. The bsmt intersection consisted of primarily pyr graph mp gn with local weak b/d deform and local peg. Local wk-str cataclasites with clasts of cord bearing mp gn and psammopelitic gn.

HolePurposeComment: To fence grid north of WC-314 piercing the unconformity approximately 30 m NW.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc member was overall str bleached with very local patchy silicification; silica healed structures; and local str pyrite noted along local fracture/bedding planes.  The MFb member was encountered at 197.1m depth with the sequence being poorly bleached and wk-mod silicified with common silica healed fractures and faults with local siderite.  The basal sequence was strongly bleached with strong black staining; patchy chloritic alteration; local strong pyrite; and local zones of pervasive argillization.  The unconformity was encountered at 430.3m.  The bsmt intersection was composed of a poorly altered mod-str structured graphitic pelitic/psammopelitic sequence with local intersections of wk-mod developed cataclasite.

HolePurposeComment: To fence grid south of WC-314 piercing the unconformity approximately 25 m SE.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc was overall str bleached and poorly structured with patchy limonite staining noted proximal to the subcrop.  Local silica healed fractures were noted throughout the upper and lower sst sequence.  The MFb member was composed of mod to poorly bleached locally silicified coarse grained sst with the basal sst being poorly bleached and unaltered with common heavy mineral bands and strong primary hematite.  The u/c was interected at 424.2m; with the contact being sharp and unaltered. The upper bsmt was composed of mod pwp psammopelitic/pelitic gneiss.  Below 489.5 m depth the bsmt was strongly structured with abundant graphitic shears and local thick intersections of graphitic cataclasite.

HolePurposeComment: To fence grid south of WC-300 piercing the unconformity approximately 50 m SE.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc was strongly bleached but poorly structured with patchy limonite staining.  Sandstone of the MFb member was intersected at 210.5m depth.  The lower sst was overall moderately to poorly bleached with local patchy moderate silicification with local zones containing common silica healed fractures and faults.  The basal sst was poorly structured and altered with a thin zone of weak mineralization noted from 425.2 to 425.3m depth.  A GT of 1.37 was calculated for the zone using a cut-off of 1permil.  The unconformity was intersected at 437.5m depth with the unconformity being sharp and unaltered.  The bsmt intersection was composed of strongly structured graphitic psammopelitic gneiss/graphitic cataclasite.

HolePurposeComment: To target the moderate conductor identified during the 2005 moving loop survey.
HoleGeneralComment: The MFc was mod-str bleached and weakly structured. The upper MFb was poorly bleached and poorly structured with a mod bleached; mod structured interval from 269-296.9 m. From 402 m the basal MFb becomes wk-mod bleached; wk structured. A sharp u/c contact at 468.9 m is followed by 20 cm of str silicified bsmt rock; a silicifed contact; 20 cm of str silicified sst and a sharp contact into the PWP at 469.3 m with no evidence of faulting or structure. The PWP is partially overprinted by mod bleaching, arg and b/d deform. The bsmt intersection consists of PsaPel and mp gneiss with narrow intervals of psammite/calcsilicates; as well as narrow cataclasite units with varying degrees of b/d deform. The bsmt is graph bearing with str remobilized graph within the cata.

HolePurposeComment: To fence 20 m south of weakly mineralized WC-303.   WC-303 sandstone column contains strongly anomalous indicators of illite and uranium partial.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper MFc was str bleached and poorly structured with wk-mod bleached lower MFc and mod structured intervals. The upper MFb was wk-mod bleached with local str bleaching and wk structured down to 404.4 m. The remaining sst column was mod-str bleached and mod structured. Argillized U/C at 460.7 m at 35 to core axis followed by a narrow PWP with weak uranium mineralization from 462.4-463.3 m. The remaining bsmt intersection consisted of primarily Cord(<5 mm)-pyrite-graphitic mp gneiss which was poorly structured overall. Quartz dissolution from 465.2-465.4 m and narrow bleached intervals from 496-497.7 m and 560.8-561.4 m. Narrow rare peg stringers throughout the bsmt intersection. Fresh biotite from 543 m.

HolePurposeComment: Microseismic hole; drilled for installation of geophones; unconformity was not intersected. Drilled by the minesite.

Test resistivity low along EM conductor.  Resistivity low occurs in sandstone and basement and trends across EM conductor.  EM coincident with boundary of interpreted mag high feature - possible granite.
HoleGeneralComment: About 61m of overburden.  Sandstone very weakly fractured.  Local bleaching and pyrite associated with fractures in upper sandstone.  Pervasive weak silica throughout sandstone.  Unremarkable unconformity at 509.7m. Basement foliation sub-parallel to core axis.  Conductor not intersected.  Resistivity low not explained.  Basement was poorly tested due to orientation of drill hole.

HolePurposeComment: To test the Andrew Lake B conductor in relation to a fault interpreted from magnetic data.  GoCAD modelling identfied the location as a secondary target area.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional sandstone with occasional silicification.  Poorly fractured sandstone. Granitic basement with typical paleoweathering profile.  295 peak gamma at 579m.

HolePurposeComment: Test Andrew A conductor along Line 24E where EM pick is coincident with Northwest resistivity low trend.  Target is on the eastern extent of Gocad defined target area.  Target was drilled before other targets due to logistical complications (not enough ice on the lake).
HoleGeneralComment: Minor structure in the upper 100m of sandstone.  Graphitic pelitic gneiss with elevated radiometrics encountered immediately below unconformity.  Up to 10% graphite but mostly disseminated.  Cordierite gneiss through much of the basement which grades into a fresh biotite-qtz gneiss (transitional gneiss with granitic sweats).  Common pyrite through most of basement.  Elevated radiometrics associated with hydro-hem and contacts with pegmatite bands in paleoweathered profile.

HolePurposeComment: To test re-interpreted Andrew-A conductor along line 24E.
HoleGeneralComment: Minor bleaching in basal sandstone. No significant structure in sandstone.  Weak and dissemated graphite in basement.  Weak to moderate pyrite.  Pelitic gneiss becoming transitional (granitic) with depth.  555cps at contact with biotite gneiss (fresh pel gn) and granitic gneiss / transitional gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: To test 2009 EM conductor and 2009 Resistivity survey resistive low.  Target generated through Gocad mineral potential mapping.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone dominantly background.  Unconformity depth (200.3 m asl) is interpreted as hanging wall to interpreted off set as defined by historical drilling.  Strongly developed red zone paleoweathering below which is graphite cordierite pelitic gneiss with narrow reactivated intervals.  Drill hole ends in granitic pegmatoid with tourmaline; variably chloritized.  Maximum probe peak of 320 cps.

HolePurposeComment: To test on section with drill hole WC-325 for possibility of basement offset as denoted by historical drilling.
HoleGeneralComment: Minor structure or alteration in the sandstone.  Graphitic peltitc gneiss with up to 10% graph below unconformity.  Faulting and common reactivation of foliation.  Strong alteration in the form of druzy quartz and bleaching near EOH.  Stopped at bit trip.  623 max downhole gamma.

HolePurposeComment: Test 2009 EM conductor and possible unconformity offset as defined by historical drill fences immediately south of WC-327.
HoleGeneralComment: Local bleaching in the sandstone.  Poorly fractured sandstone.  Abundant graphite in basement.  Remobolization of graphite with large structural and alteration zone below.  No umin.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up of structural zone intersected in WC-326.  Test for possible unconformity uranium - similar to CIG-07.
HoleGeneralComment: Weak to moderate bleaching through most of the sandstone.  Brittle structural zone from 290 to 322 m with strong bleaching and friablitiy. Minor bleaching in basement at unconformity. Rotated foliation in upper part of basement.  Altered pegmatite with remob quartz.  Drill hole seeems to have over shot unconformity expression of structure seen in the lower part of WC-326.  Low radiometrics in sandstone structure.

HolePurposeComment: Infill drilling on Waterbury Lake along strike of the Cigar East uranium mineralization.  Test for Moving Loop EM conductor on Seru Bay.
HoleGeneralComment: Fairly regional looking sandstone.  Minor brittle structure and friability in basal sandstone.  Basement is comprised of biotite gneiss with no graphite.  No umin or elevated radiometrics.

HolePurposeComment: Infill drilling on Seru Bay - east of the Cigar East mineralization.  Drilling to the south to test for possible offset of conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Rare to minor fracturing in sandstone.  Basement comprised of felsic gneisses and pegmatite.  The lower portion of the basement sections is comprised of white pegmatite with locally elevated Ra and a green mineral that is thought to be either green tourmaline - possibly spinel - or beryl.  This pegmatite intersection does correspond to a resistivity high that was previously thought to be due to a stitching error between two different surveys.

HolePurposeComment: Infill drilling on Seru Bay - east of the Cigar East mineralization.  WC-331 was also drilled to test for a possible north-south structure.
HoleGeneralComment: The sandstone is moderately fractured with zones of strong fracturing - this is uncommon for the Cigar East area.  Fracutures seem to be striking North-South or Northwest-Southeast.  The upper part of the basement is comprised of psammitic to psammo-peltic gneiss - lithologies are similar to that found in WC-307 to 310.  A pegmatite similar to the one in WC-330 was intersected in the lower part of the basement.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up structure and increased illite percentages in the sandstone of WC-311.  Further test south-thrown graphite block.
HoleGeneralComment: Bleaching and fracturing in the upper sandstone.  Weakly graphitic basement with pelitic gneiss and minor biotite gneiss.  Elevated Ra below unconformity in remobilized graphitic gneiss. Brittle fault zone near EOH.  Possibly near a cross-cutting fault.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up of WC-332 and historical hole WC-311.  Test for southern extent of graphitic package.  Follow-up structure in the sandstone column of WC-332.  Basement tectonic and alteration seem to be increasing to the south.
HoleGeneralComment: Bleaching and structure observed in upper sandstone.  Basement is comprised of weakly graphtic gneisses with minor biotite gneiss at EOH.  Occasional thin zones of brittle deformation throughout much of basement.  Alteration and quartz remob thoughout.  Inequigranular cord graph gn suggests basement is still part of Cigar East conductive package.  Slight Ra elevation in pel gn above cord gn - associated with possible black chlorite alt'n and fractures.

HolePurposeComment: Follow up of structure as seen in WC-311 and WC-332.  Test for basement lithologies and for umin.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone showing common zones of strong fracturing and bleaching.  Increased tectonics and bleaching and friability near the unconformity.  Trace hydro hematite near/above the unconformity.  Basement mainly comprised of pelitic gneiss with varying amount of graphite.  Com pyrite and other sulfides. Occasional cords - typically <1cm.  >1cm cords near bottom of hole.  Mod chl alt through much of basement with local argillization.  No umin or significant brittle structure in the basement aside from thin fault gouges.  Graphite commonly finely disseminated with local strong remoblization graphite along fractures foliation and gouges.  Common leucratic material associated with pelitic gneisses.

HolePurposeComment: Infill drilling in Cigar East area.  Test south of WC-306-244 fence - about 100 west of WC-311 uc impact.  Test for continuity of the graphitic package to the south of the mineralization and to the west of the inferred north-south fault.
HoleGeneralComment: Structured and bleached sandstone. Minor reduced grey alteration.  Minor graphite in basement. Strong chlorite alteration.  Mix of pelitic gneiss and granitoids. Not the same as the favorable" lithological package.  No umin or discreet structure in basement."
Wedge off of WC-337 at 148.2m.
Wedge off of WC-341 at 95.4m.

HolePurposeComment: Surface geotech

HoleGeneralComment: Wedge off of WC-342 at 58.5m.

HolePurposeComment: Surface geotech
New hole added due to Engineering change.
Wedge from hole WC-347.
Wedge from hole WC-348
Wedge from hole WC-349.
Surface geotech
Cigar lake surface drilling.
Wedge from CL-365 at 64.3 metres
Wedge from CL-366 at 95.5 metres.

HoleGeneralComment: Surface Geotech
Surface Geotech
Surface Geotech
Surface Geotech

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up structure of WC-327.  Spotted 100m grid east of WC-327.
HoleGeneralComment: This drill hole intersected mostly regional sandstone with a strong bleached zone and quartz dissolution from 174.2-190.4 m.  Minor structures were observed in the sandstone including a 1 cm fault at 92.5 meters dipping 14 dtca.  180.6-184.8 consisted of sand; clay and lost core.  A fault breccia was also observed at 185.7 m dipping 10 dtca.  The unconformity was intersected at 304.7 m.  The basement consists dominantly of weak to moderately graphitic pelitic gneisses. The basement is moderately altered to 391.0 m; dominantly by chlorite with little to no argillite alteration.  The basement contained numerous weak to moderate structures including intense folding from 391.7-394.0 m; and 411.0-414.7 m.  Fault/Breccias are at 442.1-442.8 m and 446.2-446.9 m.  Max gamma is 449 cps at 311.6 m.

HolePurposeComment: WC-381 was collared about 200m south of historical fence CIG-5/CIG-7/CIG-8/CIG-9/CIG-10. The 2007 EM conductor was targeted at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Only local bleaching is observed within the sandstone.  Limonite extends to 22.0 m.  Druzy quartz is observed on fractures at 30.5; 39.5; and 60.5m.  The first 40 m of sandstone is strongly silicified.  Very few structural zones with local friability and lost core.  The unconformity was intersected at 308.7m and faulted.  Fault cross cuts basement foliation.  80 cm of bleaching is observed below the unconformity; followed by 6.8m of red zone paleoweathering.  Upper basement is mainly graphitic gneiss with loc cords and weak ductile to loc strong brittle structure.  lower portion is mainly gran/peg. The bottom portion of the hole has loc metasomatic alteration (of pel gn?) and strong folding - possilbly proximal to altered structure as seen in WC-327.  No umin.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up of conductor trend south of historical drilling.  Follow-up of WC-381 to test for unconformity offset and graphite/granite contact at uc.  Also test for location of altered structure as seen in WC-327.
HoleGeneralComment: The sandstone is poorly fractured and weakly bleached.  Drusy quart noted along fractures. The basement is comprised mainly of graphitic gneiss with weak to moderate alteration (chlorite and arg) throughout most of the basement section.  Possible metasomatic alteration near EOH.  UC expression of graphitic brittle fault still to the west of the UC impact. No umin. Structure as seen in WC-327 not encoutered.

HolePurposeComment: Follow up of previous holes.  Test for structure as seen in WC-327.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone is regional" for the most part.  Minor bleaching near the UC.  Basement is comprised mainly of graphitic gneiss with brittle to brittle-ductile deformation but less than previous holes.  No umin.  Structure as seen in WC-327 not encountered."

HolePurposeComment: Test for signs of basement structure south of historical fence CIG-02 -03-04.  Begin testing conductor strike length to the south.
HoleGeneralComment: Bleaching in the upper sandstone. Basement is comprised of graphitic pelitic gneiss mixed with pegmatite and granite.  Common elongated cordierite grains.  Graphite is only weakly remobilized and usually near contacts with pegmatites.  More bleaching in upper sandstone than previous holes.  Intersected hanging wall" side of UC offset.  Structure as seen in WC-327 not encountered.  No Umin."

HolePurposeComment: Regional exploration hole collared on the same fence than WC-384. Follow-up of EM conductor. Target the unconformity in the footwall.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper sandstone is locally moderate bleached to 94.0 metres.  307-310m:  Moderate bleaching.  Otherwise weakly bleached sandstone.  Local trace to weak limonite to 36.5 metres.  Sandstone is poorly fracture to 214 m.  214.0-251.3 m shows an increase in fracturing up to 6 fractures/m with dissolution and lost core from 248.8-250.1 m.  279.0-296.0m:  Also shows increased fractures up to 6/m.  2 m of rubble at end of hole.  No significant mineralization was intersection in this drill hole.  Drill hole was not probed due to broken rods at 100 metres.  Drill rods were broken at 100 metres; and the unconformity was not intersected in this drill hole.  Drill hole ends at 321.0 m.

HolePurposeComment: Regional exploration. WC-386 was collared about 200m south of fence WC-384/WC-385. It is to test for the southern extension of the EM conductor. The strike of the E conductor is drastically changing from N00 to N45.
HoleGeneralComment: WC-326 was abandoned at 273 metres in the sandstone due to stuck rods.  Hole was not probed.  Sandstone is strongl to moderalty bleached in the upper 135m and  locally moderate to strong bleaching throughout most of sandstone.  Rarely fractured to weakly fractured.  Small zone of fracturing and friability at 22 to 31 metres.

HolePurposeComment: Re-drill of WC-386.  Test Moving Loop EM pick.  Follow-up of previous holes to the north to test for unconformity offset and graphite package.
HoleGeneralComment: Bleached sst with local fracturing and dissolution.  Loc massive clay and lost core in 11 m structural zone at 311 to 322.  Bsmt comprised mainly of gran and peg.  Mnr pel gn.  Loc graph.  Did not intersect same conductor as seen in northern drill holes.  On footwall" side of uc offset."

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up structure of WC-327.  WC-380 was lost in the basement and failed at intersecting the structure. The azimuth and dip have been set up to test for possible east-west or northeast-southwest strike of the basement structure.
HoleGeneralComment: Mod to wk bl in sst with rare fractures and weakly developed fault at 244-249m.  Bsmt is comprised pel gn with graph and loc cord and possible white to pale green calc silicate.  Two brittle faults with remob qtz and graph. WC-327 inferred structure not seen in basement.  hanging wall" side of uc offset intersecte.  No umin."

HolePurposeComment: Infill drilling of the Cigar East mineralized pod.  Test for thickness (north-south) extent of zone northeast of WC-244s mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone is bleached and fractured with increased clay alteration towards unconformity at 431.1.  The lower 10m of the sandstone is weakly mineralized with sooty disseminated pitchblende and pitchblende along veins or fractures.  Max downhole gamma is 25082cps at 428.5m.  Bsmt is comprised entirely of cord-graph pel gneiss with local evidence of ductile and ductile-brittle deformation.

HolePurposeComment: Test eastern extent along strike of Cigar East mineralized pod.
HoleGeneralComment: Mod to strongly bleached sst.  Very weak umin at and above the uc.  Radiometric GT of 3.15 (0.1% cut-off).  Deformed graphitic pyritic pel gn bsmt.  Not the same deformation as Cigar  East Pod.  Drill hole tested intended target (2 wedges used in the sandstone) however mineralization was weaker than hoped for.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up of upper sandstone geochemical and spectral anomaly as seen in the 2009 hole - WC-302.  A weakly mineralized inferred trend extending from Cigar East mineralized pod also extends into the area.
HoleGeneralComment: Hole was stopped at 48 metres due to deviation problems.  Hole restarted as WC-391A.

HolePurposeComment: Re-start of WC-391 due to deviation problems below casing.  Moved about 4 feet back from WC-391 collar.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper sandstone contains argillization and faulting.  The basal sandstone is grey and black in colour with elevated radiometrics.  The basemest is a mix of graphitic pel gn and pegmatite.  Mnr cataclasite and faulting noted.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up of mineralization as seen in WC-314 (geochem GT=57.6). Targeted Uc 100m SW of Uc intersected in WC-314. Mineralization follows basement lithology unit rather than the interpreted N100 Tibia brittle/ductile fault.
HoleGeneralComment: 32 BQ rods and 23 NQ rods lost in bottom hole. 7 3m NW rods and NW casing shoe abandoned in overburden. The lower sandstone is pervasively bleached with a thick fault zone from 381.6-405.3m.

HolePurposeComment: Follow up drill hole fence of WC-314. This hole was collared from the same set-up than WC-413 to test the structure in the sandstone of WC-413 at or near the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Brittle-ductile faulting observed from 452-455m; 494.5-497.2m; 547-551.9m and 557.2-558.3m

HolePurposeComment: Collared to test for extension of high grade mineralization 30m WSW of drill hole WC-244 and 15m S of WC-262
HoleGeneralComment: Abandoned at 123m depth due to bad deviation in overburden. Azimuth 15 degrees off to the left.

HolePurposeComment: Restart of WC-415. Collared to test for extension of high grade mineralization 30m WSW of drill hole WC-244 and 15m S of WC-262
HoleGeneralComment: The same bad deviation in WC-415 was noted (16 degrees off to the left) and several assumptions were made to explain this deviation including; 141m of NQ rods and NW rods left on top of drill hole WC-258 located 15m from WC-415A. It was decided to keep drilling past the possible magnetic effect of the steel in WC-258 but at 200m the problem remained the same. It was decided to keep drilling to test the unconformity 35m WSW of the original target. 17 3m NW rods and NW casing shoe left in overburden.

HolePurposeComment: Collared to test extension of high grade mineralization 30m WSW of drill hole WC-244 and 15m S of WC-262. WC-415A was designed to intersect this target so the drill was moved 50m to the N to steepen the hole for more effective wedging.
HoleGeneralComment: Orientation test at 66m determined the dip and azimuth were off the intended target (19 degrees left). The hole was continued to120m in hopes that with extra pressure on the drill bit the hole would steepen and turn to the east. It was determined at 120m to install a wedge to steepen the hole and then continue allowing the azimuth to correct itsel. A second wedge was installed at 150m to correct for azimuth but the obtained azimuth was off the target. A third wedge was installed above the previous wedge. The unconformity was intersected 3.0m away from original target. 18.3m NW rods and NW casing shoe abandoned in overburden. Perched mineralization along fault zone. GT=17.6m?

HolePurposeComment: Test of the 2011 Moving Loop EM anomaly
HoleGeneralComment: A regional MFd sandstone sequence was intersected below the overburden. The drill hole was lost at 90.0m depth after the core barrel became stuck at 33.0m depth.   In total 11 NQ rods; 10 10ft NW rods; 2 2ft NW rods and 1 core barrel was lost down the hole.  The hole was unable to be cemented.  The drill hole was not geochemically or petrophysically sampled and was unable to be probed.

HolePurposeComment: Test of the 2011 Moving Loop EM anomaly. Restart of WC-417.
HoleGeneralComment: A regional MFd sandstone sequence was intersected below the overburden. The drill hole was lost at 144.0m depth after the rods became stuck and were snapped.   In total 31NQ rods and 1 core barrel were lost down the hole.  The hole was unable to be cemented.  The drill hole was not geochemically or petrophysically sampled and was unable to be probed.

HolePurposeComment: Test of the 2011 Moving Loop EM anomaly. Restart of WC-417A
HoleGeneralComment: A regional MFd sandstone sequence was intersected below the overburden. Minor structuring in the upper MFd member caused the rods to be stuck at 150.0m depth.  The decision was made to advance the casing to 52.0m depth.  Due to a deviation which occurred during casing advancement coring was restarted at 51.0m depth.  The drill hole was lost at 148.7m depth along the new drill path after the rods became stuck and the drill hole was not able to be advanced.   All rods were able to be recovered and all casing was removed.  The hole was cemented from 80.0 to 50m depth.  The drill hole was not geochemically or petrophysically sampled and was unable to be probed.

HolePurposeComment: Test of the 2011 Moving Loop EM anomaly. Restart of WC-417B; drill rig moved ahead 20m.
HoleGeneralComment: Start casing with HWT and coring with HQ down to 162m in order to pass the supposed bad ground at 150m. No possibility to get Reflex survey tests in the HQ rods as the right adapter was missing. First test at 198m depth. Fault zone intersected from 239.8 to 244.5m with extensive core loss (~50%) quartz dissolution and minor clay gouge present on fracture planes. Very trace secondary hematite approx 8m above U/C. Local structures within the basement intersection (<10cm thick). Graphitic packages for >50m indicates conductive zone targeted by geophysics was accurate.

HolePurposeComment: Test of the 2011 Moving Loop EM anomaly
HoleGeneralComment: A regional Manitou Falls formation sandstone package was intersected below the overburden.  The upper sandstone was moderately bleached with a local strongly fractured zone noted from 222.4-235.8m.  The lower sandstone was very poorly bleached unaltered and unstructured.  The unconformity was intersected at 530.3m.  The upper basement is composed of paleoweathered pelitic gneiss to 541.5m depth with a weakly graphitic pelitic package noted below.  Local foliation parallel graphitic shears are noted however no discrete structural zones are evident. This weakly graphitic package which is >50m indicates conductive zone targeted by geophysics was accurate.
Cameco DDH CL-422 renamed to WC-420 because Areva DDH WC-442 already exists

HolePurposeComment: To follow up drill holes WC-312/WC-313. A major structure has been interpreted btwn these two drill holes. The bsmt of WC-312 is dominated by graphitic gneiss while in WC-313 the bsmt is dominated by psammopelitic gneiss.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 31.8m. Regional MFc and MFb sst until 242.2m. MFb at 156m. The upper sst is overall wkly to loc mod bleached. Below 242.2m the sst becomes mod to str bleached. Loc structures zones btwn 170.4 to 287.2m. The lower sst is structured/faulted from 366.7 to the Uc. The uc at 384.2m. The upper bsmt is composed of PW psammopel/pel gneiss to 395.7m. A wk to mod graph cordierite pyrite psammopel/pel gn below. No evidence of structural zones except for loc mod- strongly ductile deformed intervals and a silica healed breccia noted at 437.4-439.6m.

HolePurposeComment: To follow up drill hole WC-237. A major basement structure (graphitic shear-breccia zone) was intersected between 382.7 and 393.5 m within WC-237.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 39.3m. Regional MFc and MFb sst down to 338m. MFb at 358.1m. Patchy wk to mod bleaching. Below 338 m the sst is mod to stgly bleached with loc tr hem. Overall the sst is poorly fractured. Few structure zones at 66.8-70.8m & 171.3-185.7m. Major fault zone from 338m down to Uc w/ major core loss below 348m. Uc at 358.1m. The bsmt consisted of PW psammopel gn until 375.7m. The rest of the bsmt is a graph cordierite pyrite psammopel gn w/ common peg intervals. Variable amounts of graph are noted throughout from trace-wk to loc mod-strong. Brecciated fault zone btwn 415.2-436.6m.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2012 Moving Loop SQUID TEM conductor target. This conductor pick shows high conductivity and it is close to interpreted NW MAG lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob down to 39m. MFc sst w/ wk-mod  bleach. The upper sst was poorly structured apart from a narrow zone of increased frac and dissolution btwn 95.8-102m. MFb was intersected at 136.4 m w/ wk-mod bleach. Mod-str bleach after 315m. Competent to loc blocky and structure zones after 220m. Structuring more common below 300m. Uc at 347.8m. The upper bsmt was PW psapel gn up to 374.8m. Remaining bsmt was graphite-pyrite-cord pelitic gneiss w/ peg intervals. Fault zone from 409.6-413.6m w/ graph gouge & str fracturing.

HolePurposeComment: To follow up drill hole WC-238. This drill hole will help establish a better understating of the geology in this area by having a drill fence instead of a single drill hole.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 30.7m. Mostly regional sst (MFc and MFb). MFb at 145.9m. Mod bleaching within MFc and below 329.4m. No major structure in the sst. Blocky/de-silicif zones btwn 314.4-354.9m. Uc at 354.9m. A narrow breccia was noted below the Uc to 355.8m. PW psammopel gn btwn 354.9-362.2m. The bsmt below is composed of graph pyrite cordierite pel/psammopel gn. Weak-mod graph and pyrite until 427.8m with trace-weak below. Fresh psammopel gn below 438m with pink garnets after 444m.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2001 UTEM Moving Loop conductor target. This conductor pick shows high conductivity and it is considered a high priority target.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 34m. A regional MFc and MFb sst until 290m. MFb at 138.3m. The rest of the sst is structured w/ mod-strong fract; blocky/rubbly core; wk-mod to loc strong qtz dissolution; loc breccias/gouges; silicified sst fragments and local rotated bedding. Uc at 336.6m. The upper bsmt is composed of PW pel/psammopel gn. Loc blocky zones until 347m. Graph pyrite cordierite pel/psammopel gn w/ wk-mod graph and tr-wk sulphides below 369m. Several narrow structure zones w/ mod-strong brittle/ductile deformation.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2012 Moving Loop SQUID TEM conductor target. This conductor pick shows well defined late-time response between interpreted MAG lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 34.6m. A regional MFc and MFb sst. MFb at 137.5m. Wk-mod bleached w/ purple primary hem banding. Overall the sst is competent except for structure zones btwn 315-321 m; 328.7-329.5 m and 338-344.0 m w/ mod-strong qtz dissolution; local clay gouges/breccias; blocky/rubbly core; variable core loss and loc second hem alt. Uc at 344.5m. PW pel gneiss down to 354.2m. The rest of the bsmt is composed of graph pyrite cordierite gneiss. Wk-mod graph. Trace-wk to loc mod pyrite. Several narrow mod-strong brittle/ductile deformation zones.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2012 Moving Loop SQUID TEM conductor target. This conductor pick shows moderate conductivity and it is located between interpreted MAG lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 48.1m. MFc sst is mod bleached until 124m w/ wk-mod bleaching below. Mostly competent w/ structure zone btwn 116.9-121.9m. MFb at 130.9m. Wk-mod bleaching. Major fault zone btwn 238.7 and 257 m w/ blocky core; sandy intervals; silicified sst fragments; common clay breccias/gouges and loc rotated bedding. Uc at 340.8m. The bsmt down to 376.3 m was PW psammpel gn. The bsmt below is mostly graph pyrite cordierite pel/psammopel gn. Wk-mod graph and sulph. No graph noted btwn 423.5-447.3m; fresh psammopel gn. The bsmt is poorly fract & competent.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2012 Moving Loop SQUID TEM conductor target. This conductor pick shows good late-time response and it is close to interpreted EW MAG lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 34.8m. Below regional MFc and MFb were intersected. MFb at 139.0m.  Overall sst was poorly fract; poorly alt and competent with only a loc thin fract zone from161.5-163.5m. Uc at 356.3m. PW psammopel gn below the UC down to 368.5m. The bsmt below is weakly graph psammopel/pel gn intermixed w/ loc thin peg intervals. Graph is trace to loc wk w/ trace-wk sulphides. A local thin fract zone from 403.0-408.5m w/ common graph and chlorite coated fract. Below 409.1m fresh psammopel gn was noted for the rest of bsmt w/ loc trace graph and trace sulphides. Loc peg zones.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2003 UTEM Moving Loop conductor target. This conductor pick shows high conductivity.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 35.1m. Structured and bleached MFc sst from Ob to 51.9m. Mostly mod bleached and competent MFc sst below w/ fract zone btwn 71.5-79.6m. MFb at 144.1m. Competent wk-mod bleached regional MFb sst until 305m w/ mod bleaching below. Uc at 364.4m. PW pel-psammopel gn until 376.8m. Weakly graph cordierite pyrite pel gn w/ tr-wk graphite and sulphides. Below 413.1m fresh psammopel gn w/garnets; tr sulphides and local trace graph. Narrowl fracture zone from 357.5-359.2m otherwise competent bsmt.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2012 Moving Loop SQUID TEM conductor target. This conductor pick shows moderate conductivity and it is located close to interpreted EW MAG lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 54.1m. Wk-mod bleached MFc sst w/ increased structuring in two thin zones (84-87m; 158.9-161.5m). MFb at 166.4m. Wk-mod bleached competent sst. Uc at 388m. PW psammopel gn until 397.9m. The bsmt btwn 397.9-419.9m was graph pyrite cordierite gn. Weak-mod graph w/ trace-weak pyrite. Psammopel gn w/ trace-loc weak graphite and trace-weak sulphides btwn 426.7-443.1 m. The bsmt below 443.1 m is dominated by fresh psammopel gn w/ trace sulphides and loc trace-weakly graph gn intevals. No major bsmt structure zones.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2001 UTEM Moving Loop conductor target. This conductor pick show high conductivity and is considered a high priority target.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 76m. Regional MFc w/ wk-mod bleaching. MFb at 171m. MFb is weak-mod bleached until 318m with mod bleaching below. The sst is competent until 308 m. Below narrow blocky zones (1-3 m) loc intersected. A fault zone btwn 329.6-340.9 m w/ blocky core; mod fract; wk-mod qtz dissolution; loc clay gouges/breccias and loc rotated bedding. Another structure zone btwn 352.1-356 m. Uc at 378.2m. The bsmt down to 388.3m is PW psammopel gn. Graph pyrite cordierite psammopel gn btwn 388.3-461.1m. Wk-mod graph and sulphides until 432m w/ tr-wk below. Rest of bsmt is fresh psammopel gn.

HolePurposeComment: To follow up drill hole CIG-209. In CIG-209 structure/fault zones were observed in the upper sandstone (mostly within the top 200m) and Upartial greater than 0.5ppm was noted throughout the sandstone column.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 36.2m. MFc sst was mod to very loc wk bleached and commonly structured. Narrow blocky zones and few structure zones (83-93m; 124.3-134.5m). MFb at 147.5m. The sst was wk-mod bleached w/ loc narrow blocky zones and a structure zone btwn 304-309.5m. Uc at 364.5m. A thin PW pel gn until 370.3m. The remainder of the bsmt is composed of graph pyrite cordierite pel gn. Mostly mod-strong graph and trace-wk to loc mod sulphides. Wk-mod to loc strong brittle/ductile deformation was noted throughout especially btwn 378-393m; 409.2-420.2m; 452-456m; 464-466.3m and 467.5-471.5m. Major fault zone w/ mod-strong brittle/ductile deformation btwn 430.2-439m.

HolePurposeComment: Test the 2012 Moving Loop SQUID TEM conductor target. This conductor pick shows good late-time response and it is close to interpreted EW and NW MAG lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob down to 43.8m. MFc sst was wk-mod bleached w/ prim hem banding below 60m. MFb at 150.5m w/ wk to loc mod bleaching and common prim hem. Competent & poorly structured sst. Uc at 362.1m. The upper bsmt was PW psammopel gn down to 373.8m. Graph py pel gn btwn 373.8-460m w/ wk to loc mod graph and trace-wk pyrite. Loc chl alt cordierites. Structure zone btwn 423-424.8m w/ strong brittle/ductile deformation (cataclasite). Below 460m the bsmt consisted of psammopel gn w/ trace to loc wk graph and wk to loc mod pyrite. Common pegmatites btwn 479-501m.

HolePurposeComment: Test the low resistivity feature in basement and possible alteration in the sst. The resistivity target is close to two MAG lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob down to 38m. MFc was mod bleached and competent. MFb at 103.4m. The MFb was wk-mod bleached w/ mod bleaching below 292.5m. Enhanced friability; qtz dissolution and mod fract btwn 300-321m. Uc at 326.7m. PW pel/psammopel gn until 341.2m. Pelitic gn below w/ tr-wk sulphides and tr graphite. The remaining bsmt (362.5-481.8m) consisted of pel/psammopel gn w/ tr-wk pyrite and local garnets apart from two thick peg zones btwn 406.4-437.2m and 442-454.1m. A graph gn interval was noted btwn 374.6-377.9m with mod-str brittle/ductile deformation. After tr-wk graphite was only observed very locally over narrow zones (0.1-1.0 m).

HolePurposeComment: Test the low resistivity feature in basement and possible alteration in the sandstone. The resistivity target is close to two MAG lineaments. The unconformity is intersected about 60 m north from WC-435.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob down to 46.9m. Mod bleached and competent MFc sst. MFb at 108.1m. MFb is mostly mod bleached until 283 m; wk bleached below w/ loc mod bleaching. Narrow blocky zones (0.5-3 m thick) with mod fracturing; wk-loc mod qtz dissolution and loc core loss btwn 188.7-301.4 m. No major struct zones. Uc at 337.8 m. PW peg and pel gn until 372 m. The rest of the bsmt is composed of pegmatites/granitoids and pel/psammopel gn. Fresh bsmt below 386.2 m. Trace to loc wk-mod sulphides. Pink garnets noted throughout. Very loc tr-wk dissem to remob graphite. Competent and poorly fractured.

HolePurposeComment: To test the historical DEEPEM Fixed Loop conductor pick to the south of drill hole WC-435.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob down to 42.9m. Mod bleached MFc sst w/ blocky zones @ 48-51m & 56.2-58.9m. MFb at 94m. MFb w/ mod bl from 94-135.5m; 220-275m and 296.5-306.8m. Loc narrow blocky zones (0.5-5 m thick) w/ mod fract; tr-wk qtz dissolution; minor core loss and loc clay gouges. Uc at 306.8m. PW peg and pel gn until 339.5m. Pel/psammopel gn until 366.2m w/ tr-wk pyrite. Pel gn with tr-wk to loc mod graph and pyrite btwn 366.2-400m. Mod brecciated with loc graphitic gouges and cataclasite btwn 384.8-385.7m & 390-390.4m. The rest of the bsmt is fresh pel/psammopel gn with tr to loc wk pyrite and pink garnets.

HolePurposeComment: Fence 60m south of Uc impact hole 426 test for southern edge of graphitic trend; test potential unconformity bump and follow-up the anomalous sst in 426. The basal sandstone in WC-426 was strongly bleached; argillized and structured.
HoleGeneralComment: The sandstone column was regional in nature of alteration and structure with the basal portion being bleached. A typical paleoweathering profile was encountered. Metasedimentary rocks ranging from psammitic psammopelitic pelitic and calcsilicate were intersected. Below an anatectic pegmatoid was intersected leading into a graphite pyrite cordierite pelitic gneiss with local graphitic structures to the end of the hole. The southern edge of the graphitic package was confirmed.

HolePurposeComment: WC-439 is to test a 2012 mod strength (52.1 Siemens) MLTEM pick on line 74E - the Cigar Conductor. There is a 1400m drilling gap b/t ddh on the main Cigar conductive trend in this area. The collar is 62.5m grid S of the target.
HoleGeneralComment: The drill hole intersected a bleached sandstone column with extensive quartz dissolution causing strong friability and many zones of core loss. Local argillization is observed. The basement consists of paleoweathered graphitic gneiss that is locally structured and argillized overlying graphite pyrite cordierite pelitic gneiss which composes the bulk of the basement intersection. There are occasional narrow breccia zones intersected. The EM target was tested and confirmed.

HolePurposeComment: Test 60m south of u/c in WC-433; testing sst struc & anomalous sst ( illite & Upart) observed in WC-433 and CIG-209. To test the southern extent of graph package & obtain oriented data to determine strike & dip of bsmt & sst struc in the area.
HoleGeneralComment: The drill hole intersected weak to moderately bleached upper sandstone; mottled upper MFb and bleach altered and argillized lower sandstone with brick red hem and grey-green chloritized/reduced zones immediately above the u/c. Approx u/c at 361.5m assoc w/ massive clay and 2.9 m lost core. Graph-cord-pyr pel gn throughout the bsmt with two thin qtz-feld-bio peg. 8m red-green pwp below u/c; unit is folded and sheared. Mod to str graph 369-439m and weak thereafter. Peg sweats throughout the pel gn (10-15% loc up to 35%). Struc zone from 479-484.3m - healed shear; breccias w/ increased fracturing.

HolePurposeComment: Fence 60m north of unconformity of WC-426 to test the graphitic basement structures intersected in that hole at the unconformity. Determine the northern extent of the graphitic package. Test elevated u/c bump.
HoleGeneralComment: The sandstone displays bleached intervals and structurally controlled zones characterized by dissolution; friability; argillization & core loss. Rotated bedding is noted locally. Bsmt is a package of variably graphitic pyritic cordierite pelitic gneiss No significant structures intersected in the basement. The max downhole radiometric value of 471 cps from 218.9 metres at the basal contact of the upper structural zone intersected in the sandstone column.

HolePurposeComment: Target related to an excellent 2012 MLTEM pick. Test the extent of the graphitic package north of the historical drilling CIG-191. Geology appears to be off set to the north in this area. Location of historical collars may be questionable so this hole is spotted with the best available information
HoleGeneralComment: MFc and MFb sandstone was poorly altered overall with only local bleaching. The sandstone was poorly structured with one narrow fault zone. The basement consisted of trace to weak graphite; wk-mod pyrite +/- cordierite pelitic gneiss. Locally the graphite is moderate to strong. No significant basement structures or alteration was intersected. Location of historical fence (Cig 191; 189; 190)  potentially inaccurate.

HolePurposeComment: Fence south of 2013 drill hole WC-432. Test for  the source of anomalous illite throughout the sandstone as well structure and elevated urainum partial in the basal sandstone of hole WC-432. Test the elevated unconformity at this location. Test the southern contact of the graphitic package.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional MFc and MFb with tr to wk bleaching from 260-273m. Sandstone was poorly structured with only narrow zones of steeply dipping fractures & minor enhanced friability. Unconformity at 384.3m was a sharp contact w/ minor arg and chl. Upper basement was paleoweathered to 404.5m. Remaining basement  graphite-pyrite pelitic gneiss with trace to weak graphite and weak to moderate pyrite w/ localized cordierites. Graphite increased to wk- mod from 474.2m. Narrow pegmatites and granitoids were noted throughout.

HolePurposeComment: Drill test a strong 2012 EM pick on the Cigar B conductor proximal to interpreted structures. Closest drill test of this conductor is 1200m to the east.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional & poorly structured MFc and MFb sst to 341m w/ tr bleaching 276-328.5m. Lower sst weakly bleached from 341m; mod-str bleaching from 350m w/ loc str secondary hem/grey alt & arg from 363.5m. Upper bsmt was bleached; chl & arg with a chloritized breccia at lower contact (384.6m). Graph-cord-pyr pel gneiss extends to 434 m w/ ductile deformation (wk-str). Significant brittle/ductile struc 423.4-432.6m w/ proto to ultra-cataclasite deformatiion; str remobilized graphite; mod-str pyr; local arg & local late silicif. Remaining bsmt tr-wk graph-pyrite fine grained pel gnl increasing fresh from with depth & loc psammitic layers.

HolePurposeComment: Fence 50m north of the unconformity impact of drill hole WC-427 to test the basement graphitic structures encountered in WC-427 projected to the unconformity and to determine the northern extent of the graphitic conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Upper sandstone column is regional and poorly structured. Basal 40 meters is bleached with local remobilized hematite; local enhanced friability; brittle structuring and local clay gouges. Unconformity at 353.6 meters with two meters of bleached and chloritized pelitic gneiss beneath. Upper basement was paleoweathered with trace to weakly graphitic-pyrite pelitic gneiss below. The remaining basement was fresh biotite-rich pelitic gneiss with intervals of psammopelitic to psammitic gneiss with local cordierites.

HolePurposeComment: To test a 2003 EM pick on line 68E at station 11+00N which is also in close promixity to magnetic lineaments. This may be the SW extent of the contact conductor and would represent the first drill testing of this conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Intersected bleached and locally friable MFc and upper MFb. Below MFb was regional and poorly structured. Basal sst altered w/ loc bleaching; minor secondary hematite; grey alteration & increased friability from 364 m. PWP pel gn; 40m pegmatite which became fresh w/ depth; elevated rad near base of pegmatite (GT 8.87 24.9m @ 0.36%eU from 466.2-493.7m w/ cut-off of 0.05%eU). Biotite pelitic gneiss below & granitic gneiss at depth. Conductor was not intersected; interpreted to have overshot the ideal target.

HolePurposeComment: Test 60m north of unconformity impact hole WC-423 to test the graphitic structure encountered at depth in the basement of hole WC-423 at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional and poorly structured MFc and MFb down to 300m. Basal sst was altered w/ mod bleaching; minor remob hem; grey colored alteration; desilicification & core loss. Graphite-pyrite pelitic gneiss to 401m and fresh biotite pelitic gneiss below w/ layers of psa-pel gn and psammitic gn. Local fresh garnets. Poorly structured basement overall.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up to WC-444 cord-graph pel gn projected to u/c (S1 050/57). In WC-444 unit displayed significant ductile defmn; late brittle fracturing with remob gph; & significant brittle structure (080/60) near the base.
HoleGeneralComment: Basal 65m of sst was strongly altered w/ bleaching; arg; remob hem; grey alt and significant structure (clay gouges; flt; fracs; rot bedding; loc silic and loc desilic). Trace Umin above the u/c 2.1m at 0.17%eU from 377.5m with a 0.05% cut-off. Bleached upper basement. Upper bsmt was f gr wk graphitic pel gn with lower cord-pyrite pel gn with loc graphite below.

HolePurposeComment: Follow-up and intersect the u/c between WC-433 and WC-440. Both drill holes had elevated counts at the u/c; anomalous sst alteration and graphitic bsmt. Targeted to intersect the structure observed in WC-433 at depth.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional upper sst w/ local struc zones; enhanced friability and argillization. The basal 75m of sst is altered and structured w/ common bleaching; loc remob hem; argillization and grey 'reduced' zone. Slightly elevated basal sandstone; max 250cps at 355.4m. U/C at 362m. Weakly overprinted pwp. Variably graphitic-pyrite +/-cord pelitic gneiss. Local psammitic layers at depth w/in biotite-rich pelitic gneiss. 15m brittle fault zone (damage zone?) with cataclasite (15m thick) below (corresponding to structure observed in WC-433). Qtz bx (10m thick) below and flt gouge at lower contact; common remobilized graphite.

HolePurposeComment: Test anomalous Upartial + illite in WC-433; & up-dip expression of bsmt structures in WC-433. Test northern extent of graphitic package. CIG-209 to the northwest (off section) also had anomalous Upartial in the sandstone.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional upper sandstone with variable bleaching from 254m down to the u/c at 368m. Approx 10m structure zone at 252m w/ blocky core and core loss. Wk overprint of pwp; still persists to 388m. Basement comprised of cordierite-graphite-pyrite pelitic gneiss; psammopelitic gneiss and pegmatite intervals. Variable anatectic sweats; locally >50%. Upper basement is weak-moderately structured to 451m with local faults with remob graphite and slickensides. At least two dominant fracture sets; one low angle TCA and sub// S1 w/ common graphite and strike slip movement and one high angle TCA often containing clay/chlorite/pyrite.

HolePurposeComment: Test east extent of Cigar East graphitic package south of hole WC-331. There is a change in geology to the west where granitic rocks were encountered (possible offset or folded). Test source of illitic sst in WC-331.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional upper sandstone with dominant bleaching below 286m with local remobilized hematite and wk silicification (and faint grey tinge) below 386m. Structure interval from 293-303m with minor associated desilicification. U/C at 397.2m w/ rubbly sst above and arg; bleached bsmt below. Basement is comprised of graphite-pyrite-cordierite pelitic to psammo-pelitic gneiss and common pegmatoid intervals. Weak to loc mod graphite appears at depth (441.3m) 45m below the u/c. Zones of strong anatectic sweats. Common foliation parallel fractures throughout the upper basement down to 441m with rare fractures below and local foliation 35-50TCA.

HolePurposeComment: Test a 2012 moderate EM pick on line 74E; ~350m northwest of where a graphitic package was intersected along drill fence WC-450_433_449_440. Possibly a significantly wide graphitic package or 2 separate conductors.
HoleGeneralComment: Bleached MFc with regional MFb down to 246.5m. Dominant bleaching and large structure zones below with increased alteration from 354.2 to the u/c at 362.5m. Struc from 246.5-305m and 334.3-362.5m w/ two fault/brecciated zones at 298.2 and 304m. Basal sst is grey altered with remobilized hematite and elevated RA. Max counts of 3150cps (on scint) at 362.3m. Wk bleaching; hyrdo hem; loc lim and chl overprint the pwp with elevated RA up to 305cps at 364.3m. Basement is composed of pelitic to psammo-pelitic gneiss and calc-pelite (?). Tr-wk graph and loc remob gr with loc cord. Undulating/wavy foliation in the upper bsmt. B/d struc throughout of varying intensity with cataclasite from 378.7-379.9m and 429.7-431.7m.

HolePurposeComment: Follow up mineralization intersected in hole WC-448. Test between unconformity intersections of holes WC-444 and WC-448.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional upper sandstone with bleaching becoming dominant from 304.5m and local secondary hematite and structurally controlled argillization and pale yellow/green color (possibly illite) with local clay gouges from 312 to u/c.
