Grey colored alteration from 365.3m to the u/c at 374.75m. Bsmt is comprised of pelitic to psammopelitic gneiss and pegmatite. Trace to weak graphite; pyrite and local chalcopyrite. Possible 5m thick calc-pelite w/ strong calcite veining at 472.3m. Local thin cataclasite bands; shears and proto-mylonite exist throughout with 30cm proto-cataclasite at 451m w/ sharp contact at 30TCA.

HolePurposeComment: Test structured sandstone and elevated illite in WC-439 at the unconformity 30m to the south.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional upper sandstone with dominant bleaching zones from 117-210m and local zones below related to structural intervals. Friable and desilicification common from 131.7-155m and 170-208m with variable silicification from 110-129m. Altered basal sandstone from 335.6-363m with strong bleaching and abundant core loss. U/C at ~363m; washed away and altered. Basement comprised of altered upper pegmatite with pelitic gneiss and local calc-pelitic gneiss below. Trace to locally weak graphite was intersected. Brittle fracture zones were intersected in the basement roughly parallel to foliation and with remob graph at depth. Fractures are commonly steep at 0-30d TCA.

HolePurposeComment: Fill geology gap between holes WC-319 and WC-304. Both of those holes display elevated uranium partial and illitic clay in the sandstone. Test potential mineralization between the Cigar main ore body (to the west) and the Cigar East pod (to the east).
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone is commonly bleached with limited additional alteration and structure. Minor secondary hematite and elevated counts (100cps with SPPy) in the basal sandstone at 455.7m. U/C at 460.6m. Chloritized and argillized pelitic gneiss below the u/c; anat peg w/ frequent pelitic layers. Graphitic pyrite pelitic gneiss w/ loc cordierites from 466.8m to 588m. Foliation is consistent at 30-40TCA. Local b/d deform w/ polished graphite along structure planes.

HolePurposeComment: Fence WC-439 to the north to test the basement structures and ductile deformation in the basement at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Poorly altered MFc. Common desilicification and enhanced friability with significant core loss throughout the MFb. Local argillization and trace grey alteration in the basal sandstone. Upper basement is argillized and bleached. Elevated rad (300cps with SPPy) at 369.3 and 371.9m w/in alt bsmt (possibly alt calc-silicate?). Weakly graphitic +/- cordierite pyrite pelitic gneiss and localized increases in anat sweats. Basement was poorly structured overall.

HolePurposeComment: To test the northrn continuation of the condctr + the thckns + up-dip projection of the dctl defrmtn wthn the cord graph pel gn intrsctd at the base of WC-441. Tst the strng incrs in illt alt nrth alng the sectn + mnr elvtd Upartial.
HoleGeneralComment: Mottled hematite throughout the upper sandstone with altered basal sandstone - bleached; argillized and structured. Completely argillized upper basement. Remnant paleoweathering profile below strong argillization and cordierite-graphitic pelitic gneiss below with moderate graphite. Trace to weak disseminated graphite pelitic gneiss below down to the end of hole.

HolePurposeComment: Initial test of the Powerline Centre grid. Testing resistivity feature along L800W. Resistivity low feature in the basement and possible extention up into the sandstone indicating sandstone alteration.
HoleGeneralComment: Regional sandstone throughout with local diagenetic silicification. Sharp intact unconformity. Alternating layers of non-graphitic to weakly graphitic pelitic gneiss. Common granitic sweats and local pegmatite intervals. Local zones of ductile shearing and remobilized graphite observed in pelitic gneiss intervals.

HolePurposeComment: To test the cord-graph pel gn + graphtc strctr intersected at the base of WC-422 prjctd to the U/C. Increased illite + Upartial is obsrvd in WC-422 cmprd to WC-312 + 313 to the south; providing additional vectors to the north.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper sandstone was poorly altered with only local fault zones in sandstone. Unconformity was unaltered and intact; basement consisted of weak to moderately graphitic pelitic gneiss with a quartz breccia and trace disseminated graphitic pelitic gneiss below. The basement was poorly altered throughout.

HolePurposeComment: Test assymetric resistivity low feature along L200E in the basement and possible extention up into the sandstone indicating sandstone alteration.
HoleGeneralComment: Strongly altered sandstone with a 40m thick fault zone in the upper MFc with strong bleaching; grey alteration; desilification; argillization. Sandstone was variably bleached throughout with localized structured/desilicified intervals and local pyrite (reduced) structures. The basement consisted of fine to very fine grained psammitic gneiss with local pelitic gneiss intervals. Very trace graphite was noted along structure planes and local trace disseminated pyrite.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to south of WC-452 to follow-up the weak mineralization, sandstone structure and alteration, and argillization in the lower sandstone and at the unconformity. ***3 m shift up applied to all fields; original data exported from arc expquery & shifted.
HoleGeneralComment: MFc and upper MFb sandstone were regional with local m-scale rubbly to blocky fracture zones. Lower MFb sandstone was moderately to strongly bleached and blocky with local strong clay replacement and secondary hematite at 324.5m and moderately to strongly grey reduced alteration in the basal sandstone. Paleoweathering profile largely overprinted by moderate to weak bleaching and strong to moderate chlorite. Basement lithologies consist of fine- to medium-grained trace to weakly graphitic +/- cordierite pelitic gneiss. Large incohesive to cohesive cataclastic faults intersected from 427.2 to 428 metres and 453.3 to 456 metres.

HolePurposeComment: Fence WC-460 to follow up on brittle sandstone structures with reduced alteration projected down dip to the unconformity and to test the low resistivity feature in the basement.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone column was competent with moderate to weak beaching throughout the MFc and upper MFb and regional looking and weakly bleached in the lower MFb. Intact paleoweathering profile locally overprinted by bleaching preferentially in granitic gneiss. Basement consists of fresh locally garnetiferous pelitic to psammitic gneiss with local dm- to m-scale intervals of foliated granite. Traces of graphite observed between 350 to 364m. Drill hole does not explain interpreted resistivity feature in the basement.

HolePurposeComment: Test the EM pick along L6500E at station 600. Interpreted to be mapping the graphitic cataclasite structure observed in WC-444 to the NW and WC-452 to the SE.
HoleGeneralComment: Intersected bleached upper MFc with structure controlled and interstitial pyrite. Weakly altered lower MFc and upper MFb with mottled primary hematite bands remaining. Strongly altered basal sandstone with strong bleaching; argillization and desilicification with grey alt immediately above the u/c. Bleached upper basement overprinting the PWP with only remnant PWP over meter scale intervals. Pelitic and psammo-pelitic gneiss with local trace disseminated graphite and very localized weak graphite and only minor remobilized graphite along local structure planes. Disseminated pyrite throughout. Ends in fresh garnet bearing-biotite pelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: To test north of the original resistivity target along L200E to determine an explanation of the resistivity target in the basement. Sandstone alteration exists in both drill holes along the section (WC-460 & WC-462) with sandstone structure being enhanced in the northern drill hole (WC-460).
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone is on average weakly fractured and affected by significant bleaching and argillization. Some fractures corridors associated with desilicified facies. Paleoweathering profile is overprinted by moderate bleaching and argillization in the upper part. Basement consists of anatectic psammopelitic lithologies injected ~50% by foliated granite.  All basement is affected by weakly ductile shearing, no major brittle deformation (fracture corridors and veining). Lithologies are competent and low altered below the paleo weathered zone. No graphite was observed, few traces of pyrite. No probing due to technical issues.

HolePurposeComment: Testing a strong EM pick on L6500E from the 2015 survey. Targeted along strike from weak mineralization intersected at the unconformity in WC-448.
HoleGeneralComment: Hole lost due to driller error.

HolePurposeComment: Testing a strong EM pick on L6500E from the 2015 survey. Targeted along strike from wk mnrlztn intersected at the U/C in WC-448.  ***3 m shift down applied to all fields; original data exported from arc expquery & shifted.
HoleGeneralComment: Local breccia/protobreccia intervals & local weak fracturing through weakly bleached competent sst. 49.0 to 51.2 m - reduced pyrite (locally preserved) and platy mm scale siderite related to structure. The UC is sharp with SPPY peak of 250 cps (Probe peak of 2897.1 cps at 400.9 m); mod bleached; mod argillized & weakly chloritized. Bsmt is dominantly tr-wk graphitic pelitic gneiss with subdominant fine grained pel gneiss w/ local garnetite & pegmatite intersections. Significant brittle faulting from 508.4 to 512.2 meters - characterized by sub-rounded quartz clasts suspended within black matrix w/ abundant polished graph on frac/flt planes.

HolePurposeComment: Fencing WC-458 to the north to test the centre of the resistivity feature along L800W. WC-458 did not explain the resistivity feature and was interpreted to be hanging wall.
HoleGeneralComment: Upper sandstone was weak to moderately bleached with local weak remanent hemaite. Common structurally controlled pyrite along fracture planes. Drill hole started producing water at 213m and the hole was lost due when the rods became stuck.

HolePurposeComment: Fencing WC-458 to the north to test the center of the resistivity feature along L800W. WC-458 did not explain the resistivity feature and was interpreted to be hanging wall.
HoleGeneralComment: WC-466A intersected competent moderately bleached MFc and MFb Sst to 188m with local S0 to fracture controlled pyrite and regional MFb Sst from 188m to the Uc at 342m. Below the Uc variably anatectized weak to trace graphite pelitic gneiss with minor intervals of foliated granite was intersected to 435m. Garnetiferous biotite pelitic gneiss was intersected to 447.2m and foliated granite was intersected to the EOH at 501m. The basement exhibited local ductile shearing often along lithological contacts and several ~10-15cm incohesive protobreccias were intersected throughout metasedimentary lithologies. Graphitic lithologies exhibiting ductile deformation are sufficient to explain basement resistivity low feature.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test the conductor pick on L5900 from the 2015 ML TEM survey; interpreted to be the northwest extent of the cataclasite structure intersected in WC-444 and to the southeast in WC-452.
HoleGeneralComment: The upper sst is weakly to moderately bleached; 398.2 m to the uc strong to moderate bleaching is observed. Minor structure occurs though the sandstone. Basal conglomerate from 400.0-416.6 m & is weakly argillized with short intervals of trace pervasive limonite. UC is sharp, weakly argillized, mod bleached & mod chloritized. Bsmt is dominantly graphitic pelitic gneiss until approx 460m followed by dominantly psammopelitic gneiss to the EOH with several pegmatitic intersections. Bsmt faulting is observed between 434.4- 435.2m & 513.5-515.5 m with several other intersections of mod structure perhaps peripheral to major structure. Probe peak of 755 cps in the basal sst at 407m.

HolePurposeComment: To test the up-dip expression of the brittle graphitic fault intersect at depth in WC-465A at the unconformity. Interpreted to potentially offset the unconformity and sandstone contacts to the north (south side up).
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone is very competent and poorly fractured, no significant deformation was observed. MFc is moderately bleached; MFb is bleached in the lower part. Remobilized hematite associated with elevation of radiometry in basal conglomeratic sandstone. Paleoweathering profile is preserved. Anatectic graphitic pelitic gneiss from ~ UC to 470m, weakly argillized with local evidences of ductile shearing. Graphitic fault zone connected to same in well WC-465A. Sheared psammopelitic lithologies from 470m to EOH.  Several granite-pegmatite intervals.

HolePurposeComment: To test the up-dip expression of the brittle graphitic fault intersected in WC-465A and WC-468 at the unconformity. Interpreted to potentially offset the unconformity and sandstone contacts to the north.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone is relatively competent and poorly to weakly fractured. Fractured corridor was intersected from 365 to 405 m in association with sandstone moderate alteration facies (bleaching, desilicification and argillization). Sharp unconformity at 411.2m, basal conglomerate low altered and paleoweathering profile is preserved. Large pegmatite and sheared graphitic lithologies were intersected in the upper part (traces of graphite down to 488m) and psammitic and calcsilicates from 488 to 510m (EOH).

HolePurposeComment: Testing a strong EM conductor pick on L7100E; close proximity to 3 mag lineaments (NE; NNW & ESE). Along strike from WC-454; 439; 456 fence-sign sst desilic; anomalous alt & geochem loc in the bsmt & loc elev rad in bsmt of 456.
HoleGeneralComment: Below 295 m the core shows mod to loc str bleaching to the u/c. Several sign intervals of struc appear in the sst column. Trace pyrite appears on fracture surfaces between 60.3 and 61.1m. The unconformity is strongly argillized and obscured in proximity of core loss with a weak chloritic overprint. The basement package consists of anatectic to metatectic pelite ? graph dominantly appears as wk dissmn until 441.0m past which it occurs as trace disseminations. A hydraulic carbonate breccia is observed between 382.3 and 382.5m. A significant brittle fault with mod to str polished remobilized graph b/t 418.9 and 421.8 m. Max gamma was 618 cps at 365.4m.

HolePurposeComment: To test the strong basal sst alt in WC-463 at the u/c. WC-463 tested an EM pick & was interpreted to have overdrilled the conductor. Along strike b/t the graphitic cataclasite intersected in WC-444 and WC-452.
HoleGeneralComment: Upper sst was bleached w/ pyr along frac and S0 planes down to 51m. Poorly altered and structured below down to 382.5m w/ loc silica flooded flts 252-260m. Wk-mod bleached lower sst apart from basal cong 382.5-397.1m. U/C at 397.1m. Bleached & chloritized upper bsmt to 399.3m w/ remnant pwp to 409m w/ wk overprinting. Weak graph pel gn and mod-str remobilized 412-502m. Common narrow protocataclasites; cataclasites; & graphitic clay gouges. Qtz-feld-bio peg (2-5m thick) and fol granite 531-538m. Pel to psa-pel gn w/ tr dissmn graph & minor remob w/ local cordierites 502-540m.

HolePurposeComment: To test a moderate EM pick on L116E which is interpreted to represent the Cigar conductor shifted to the north and a change in trend (not perpendicular to the N-S EM line).
HoleGeneralComment: The sst column is competent; relatively unstructured weakly; and bleached until 326 m followed by moderate bleaching until the unconformity. Strong bleaching appears in the basal sst with occasional intervals of red remobilized hematite and local massive clay replacement, and trace to weak pervasive chloritic overprint.  A possible altered bsmnt wedge occurs between 334.31 and 334.80 m with gouged and argillized contacts.  Max radiometry of 305 cps at 334.4 m in proximity to bsmnt wedge. The bsmnt lithology is dominantly GraphPelGn. There is no major fault interval within the bsmnt but sporadic sub-horizontal TCA fault planes.

HolePurposeComment: Initial test of the contact conductor to determine the nature of the conductor. Testing a moderate EM response from the 2015 SQUID MLTEM survey on L9500E.
HoleGeneralComment: Intersected str-mod bleached MFc sst and locally mod bleached MFb sst. Patchy wk to mod silicification b/t 278 and 303m. Bsmt lithologies consisted of a large interval of graph pelitic gneiss with several larger intervals of peg followed by psa-pel gn + massive calc-silicate. Graph occurred as weak dissmns to mod both within intervals cord augen gn + within brittle fault planes and protocataclastic fault zones throughout the graph pelitic gn package. Throughout the graphitic lithologies abundant ductile shearing was noted along with brittle ductile protocataclastic faulting & brittle reactivations often with polished graphitic fault planes.

HolePurposeComment: To follow-up the bleached and altered upper basement intersected in WC-472 up-dip at the unconformity and the elevated radiometry intersected in WC-472 (305cps at the u/c).
HoleGeneralComment: Mottled wk to loc mod bleaching appears until 325.5m followed by mod bleaching until the u/c at 348.9m. Weak siderite is visible on select fractures between 213 and 280 m.The basal sst from 341.90 to 348.90m has frequent heavy mineral laminea - the unit has a faint green tinge due to tr to wk pervasive chlorite.  The u/c at 348.9m is sharp at 60 TCA. Bsmt lithologies include graph pel gn +/- cord until 451.5 m followed by cordi bearing pel gn with loc tr diss graph and sporadic garnets to the EOH at 471m. Overall the sst and bsmt is poorly structured. The max gamma value recorded was 874.2 cps in the upper bsmt at 361.7m.

HolePurposeComment: Test the northeast extent of the Cigar B Conductor; testing the graphitic package at the U/C to determine the characteristics and strike of the conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Strongly bleached MFc sst and mod bl MFb sst to 198.6m followed by regional sst with short local mod bl intervals towards the Uc. Weak to trace patchy silicification was intersected between 243-290m and pyrite was obs on a fracture at 53.7m. A large variably graph to biotite pelitic gn was intersected to 508.3m followed by psammopelitic gn and calc-silicate to EOH at 513m. Graphite occurs as trace to weak dissmns and weak to mod dissmns locally within wk ductile sheared fabric btwn 399-432.5; 481.1-488m; and 502-508.3m. Both the sst and bsmnt were competent and poorly structured; the basement exhibited weak ductile shearing throughout..

HolePurposeComment: Testing an EM pick on L108 from the 2015 ML SQUID TEM survey. The pick is shifted ~100m to the south compared to adjacent lines.
HoleGeneralComment: Upper sst mod bleached down to 125m w/ local brittle frac and minor desilic. Poorly altered sandstone below w/ wk bleaching and local brittle fracs. U/C at 352.5m; pwp pelitic gn to 384m; meta and diatexite to 422.5m. Pelitic to psa-pel gn to 537m w/ local tr diss graph. Phlogopite-rich calcsilicate from 494-516m. Graphitic (weak) pel gn 516-564m w/ local protocataclasite & thin incohesive flt gouge at 554m. Porph cord graph (mod) pyr pel gn 554-564m. Borehole EM was run on the drill hole to identify any offhole response near the top to determine the ~150m discrepancy in the ground EM pick.

HolePurposeComment: Test Contact conductor along L116E in close proximity to interpreted cross cutting mag lineaments.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone is wk-str bleached w/ common buff/grey color. Scattered limonite from 360-390m. Weakly structured sst. U/C at 400.3m with pwp pel gneiss to 418.5m. Fine grained pel gn 418.5-435.6m with elevated rad from 418.5-423.6m with increased rad along frac. Qtz-feld-garnet+/-tour peg 435.6-452.7m and while fol granite (k-spar-plag-qtz-amphibole-garnet) 452.7-501m. Tr Umin along a fault from 461.3-461.8m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing for the source of the elevated Upartial and radiometry in the middle sandstone of WC-465A down dip at the unconformity. WC-465A returned Upartial values up to 126ppm from a systematic sample between 190-210m.
HoleGeneralComment: Sst wk-mod bleached to 120m. Poorly alt 120-225m. Bleached & struc 237-246m. Wk bleach 246-339m. Str bleach below w/ arg; loc remob hem; loc grey alt 339-385m. Remob hem & bleach 385.5-392m. Psa-pel 392-432m w/ mod bleaching to 400m. Pel gn from 432-540m - trace to weak graphite and loc wk-mod; zones of fresh bio-rich gneiss; loc garnet porphyroblasts. Well fol - generally NE trending and SE dipping; loc N-S strike in the pw zone. Wk ductile shearing loc from 464-480m and minor b/d deform (protocataclasite) over 30cm at 468.4m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing a double EM pick on L8900E from the 2015 ML SQUID TEM survey where an interpreted NW crosscutting structure offsets the Cigar conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Wk bleached upper sst. Str alt from 270.3 to u/c at 366.15m - str bleach; loc str desilic; loc str arg; loc core loss; loc secondary hem. Alt upper bsmt to 395.8m w/ mod-str bleach & arg throughout pel gn & granitoid. Mix of graph pel gn and non-graphitic fresh bio gneiss - interlayered. Graph-pyr pel gneiss intervals w/ common weak disseminated graphite and mod to local str remobilized graphite. Multi metre-scale protocata and metre-scale cataclasite; mod-str remob graph; loc qtz flooding; & str massive pyr over 50cm.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the resistivity low feature along L104 from the 2002 Pole-pole survey and to test the possibility of continuous or semi-continuous graphitic layer across the Cigar corridor.
HoleGeneralComment: Poorly alt upper sst. Str alt from 353.3m to the u/c at 382m w/ mod-str bleach; decimeter clay gouges; rotated block of sst; loc remob hem; sign core loss; & loc str arg. Massive cl replacement and gouges from 373.2-377.4m. Alt u/c with flt gouge. Wk-mod overprinted pwp down to 408.3m. Mixed bsmt litho w/ graph pel gn; psa-pel gn w/ variable anat sweats throughout. Graph ranges from tr-wk and mod diss and loc mod-str remob along struc and fol planes. Multi metre-scale protocata w/ str graphite and common polished graph surfaces throughout.

HolePurposeComment: Test a historical EM conductor pick on L22E; fence directly west of the last Phase 2 fence on the Cigar deposit. To test for sst alt and the presence of the cigar graphitic package to the west of Phase 2 and the extension of mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 15m; surficially bleached then buff coloured upper MFc w/ wk bleaching & wk hem. Regional lower MFc & upper MFb. Mod-str bleaching in MFb below 486m; reduced alteration & an interval of weak mineralization from 534-547m w/ assoc clay replacement; hydrothermal hematite & abundant core loss. Mod overprinted pwp; altered psammo-pelitic gneiss; potentially psammitic gneiss; fresh pel to psa-pel gn and weakly graphitic pel gn with intervals of protocataclastic deformation & cataclastic faults w/ mod structural graphite. Homogeneous peg to EOH at 681m. 4.1m @ 0.13%eU b/t 533.6 and 547m using cut-off of 0.05%.

HolePurposeComment: To test a coincident EM and resistivity target along L5400W on the Powerline North conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 92 m. Altered and structured sst down to 396 m w/mod to str fracturing, local argillized fault zones, and local brecciation from 101.6 to 138 m, from 173.2 to 178.7 m, 206.3 to 331 m, and 374.1 to 387 m. UC is a sharp unaltered contact at 476 m w/regional basal sst above and a regional paleoweathering profile below. Mixed f-gr GnPelw/ tr graph & pyrite and med-gr GnPelw/ wk graph. Graphite is primarily disseminated. The bsmt is poorly structured overall. Fresh below 596 m w/ fresh biotite and garnets throughout. Radiometric peak of 343 cps at 476 metres at the unconformity.

HolePurposeComment: To test the possible extension of the mineralization intersected in WC-481 to the north on L2200W west of Phase 2.
HoleGeneralComment: Surficial bleaching to 39m w/ wk-mod bleaching below. Mod-str bleaching from 331m (167m thickness) to the u/c w/ grey reduced alt and argillization. Competent sst column w/ m-scale struc zones and loc desilicification. U/C at 498.1m. PWP pel to psa-pel gn with phlogopite bearing psammitic gneiss below. Pel to psa-pel gn below with loc trace graphite; wk disseminated graphite and loc moderate remobilized graphite from 566.9-573.65m. Competent basement apart from 568.1-573.65m w/ cataclasitic faulting; 20cm breccia w/ graphitic clay matrix at 573.4m. Probe peak of 267 cps.

HolePurposeComment: To test the coincident EM and resistivity targets along L5400W on the Powerline South conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Hole was restarted as 484-A due to excessive deviation.

HolePurposeComment: To test the coincident EM and resistivity targets along L5400W on the Powerline South conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Wk-mod bleaching throughout sst. Semi-frequent intervals of structurally controlled dissolution causing rubbly zones and minor core loss. 147-148.4m a clast supported breccia. 212-213 str arg & bleaching. Basal 3m of basal cong are mod bleached w/ wk dissolution. U/C at 465.8m. PWP orthogneiss to 510m w/ narrow pegmatite stringers w/ clay replaced feldspars. Below 510m granitic gneiss w/ fresh biotite. No significant structure. Foliation is approx parallel TCA and dips ~60 to the southeast - opposite to the original geophysical interp. NGRS peak of 352cps. Televiewer & resistivity.

HolePurposeComment: Test the possible extension of the umin intersected in WC-481 to the south, testing for the bsmt root of the structure related to the umin and sst alter on L2200. Gain a better understanding of the bsmt stratigraphy in the Cigar West area.
HoleGeneralComment: Surficial bleaching to 47.5m. Regional looking sst below w/ only tr-wk bleaching and local m-scale zones of bleaching assoc w/ struc. Local limonite and pyrite 215.4-273.2m. Competent apart from 50cm bx at 273.5m. U/C at 534m. Pel to psa-pel gn to 628m w/ reg pwp; loc garnet; loc tr graphite and loc m-scale intervals of wk graphite. Calcsilicate gn below w/ calcite veining to 641.55m. Phlogopite psammitic gn below to EOH at 657m. Competent and poorly struc bsmt apart from brecciated interval 570.2-570.75m and clay gouge at 581.5m. Probe peak of 2144 cps assoc w/ clay gouge.

HolePurposeComment: Testing a coincident moderate EM conductor pick on L5200W and a resistivity target along the Powerline North conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Mod-str bleaching to 67.1m. Wk bleachng  and mod diagenetic hem below to 183.8m w/ wk-mod silicification from 116.2-370.7m. Basal cong is wk-mod bleached and reduced w/ loc dissolution. U/C 407.6m. Flt gouge and breccia to 409.3 w/ strong remob hem extending down to 411.4m. Pelitic gn to 456.1m w/ tr graphite (loc mod graphite from 425-433.5m) Interlayered w/ deci to m-scale granite and pegmatites. Granite from 456.1-474.7m w/ accessory garnet and biotite w/ clay and chl alt feldspars. Loc garnetiferous pel below interlayered w/ fresh granite; increasing granite and less pel gn with depth.

HolePurposeComment: To test a weak conductor pick on L1400E along the Cigar Main conductor west of Phase 2.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 49.8m. Surficial bleaching to 60m with regional sandstone below apart from moderate to strong bleaching from 402.1 to 474.3m. U/C at 515.6m is sharp and unaltered. Pwp fine grained metasediment and calc-silicate gneiss to 539m. Calc-silicate extends to 551m. Pelitic to psammo-pelitic gneiss below down to 627.8 with very trace loc graphite from 525.1-528.1m; typically non-graphitic and fresh. Local narrow proto-breccias; typically over ~20cm. Second calc-silicate at depth from 627.8m to the EOH at 645m. Borehole EM probing was conducted - no conductor was identified.

HolePurposeComment: To test south of WC-482 to determine the thickness and extent of the graphitic pelitic package in the area and to test the down-dip extent of the extensive sandstone structure intersected in WC-482.
HoleGeneralComment: Wk to mod blch to 112.7m with wk dq & sooty pyr from 57.8-105m. Structure zone from 105-112.7m. Local wk silicific. MFb is wk to mod blecahed w/ tr-wk silicific; poorly structured. Conglomeratic sst from 426.8-439.4m - wk dissolution & wk-str blch. Basal sst is strongly blchd & altered U/C at 439.4m w/ str arg & blch to 441.1m. Wk pwp below to 467.1m. Tr diss graph w/in f-gr GnPel 467.1-591.8m; weak diss graph from 491.8-527.3m w/in cr-gr GnPel. Mod graph from 527-550.4m w/in cr-gr cord GnPel w/str anatexis. Wk graph pel gn 550.4-582m coarse w/ str anatexis becoming f-gr from 580.1m. Loc less than m scale GnPsa zones near EOH.

HolePurposeComment: To test a moderate conductor pick on L1800E along the Cigar Main conductor; approximately 800m west of Phase 2 and 400m west of the weak mineralization intersected in WC-481. First attempt was restarted due to dip deviation.
HoleGeneralComment: Hole Lost.

HolePurposeComment: To test a moderate conductor pick on L1800E along the Cigar Main conductor; approximately 800m west of Phase 2 and 400m west of the weak mineralization intersected in WC-481. First attempt was restarted due to dip deviation.
HoleGeneralComment: First attempt restarted due to dip deviation. Sst is competent w/poor structure. The upper MFc is mod bleached to regional with depth. MFb is poorly altered & regional apart  from 337-412 m w/mod blch. UC at 482 m ? sharp & unaltered.The bsmt consists of a fn to loc med gr pelitic to locally GnPsaPel; poorly altered throughout apart from narrow intervals with increased chl and minor qtz dissolution ? most notably associated with breccia at 495. Intersections w/calcareous banding noted throughout. Graph is typically restricted to tr dissem flecks & is locally remob'd. NGRS peak of 504 cps at ~495m.

HolePurposeComment: To test the remodelled geophysical conductor dipping to the southeast and the coincident resistivity target on L5400 along the Powerline South conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Alternating intervals of mod blchd & regional looking sst. Loc several m intervals of blocky to rubbly  fractured core. Basal sst mod desilicifed and arg'd creating intervals w/abundant lost core and local red hydrothermal(?) hem. Mod arg & chl upper bsmt with PWP mod overprinted and w/ local fautls/fractures w/ str white talc-like mineral fill. Bsmt a mix of GnPel & pegmT followed by an interval of GnGran at depth. Tr to mod dissem and/or remob graph was intersected over several larger intervals of structured GnPel. Structure consists of early ductile shearing and later semi-brittle faulting/shearing and late brittle fracs/gouge.

HolePurposeComment: To test the up-dip expression of the semi brittle graphitic structure intersected at depth in WC-481 and 483 at the unconformity along strike from the graphitic package intersected in the most western fence of Phase 2.
HoleGeneralComment: Wk to mod blchd MFc. Regional MFb down to 333m. Wk to mod blch to 466m & str blch below to the u/c with weakly elevated radiometrics. Loc struc 208-216m; 483.5-491.7 and 497.8-501.1m w/ local arg and/or desilic.  U/C at 513.6m. Pwp is completely overprinted. Wk-mod graphitic GnPel to 538.1m w/ wk to mod arg; mod to str chl; very local hydrothermal hem and local elevated radiometry. PegmT to 574m. Pelitic to GnPsaPel w/ loc trace graph to EOH at 642m. Interlayered GnCaSi from 622.2m. Trace umin in the lower sst & upper bsmt - 0.2m at 0.06%eU from 503.8 to 505.9m and 1.4m at 0.1%eU from 514.1 to 517.8m.

HolePurposeComment: To test a strong EM pick on L1000E along the Cigar North conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Mod to str bleaching to 250.3m; wk to mod to 373.5m; and mod to str to the Uc at 543 m. Mod to str Sst structure from 374-507m as blocky to rubbly fractured/faulted core; a large breccia interval from 456.8-486.2m; and a clay gouged interval with local remob hem from 486.2-507m. Bsmt is fn-cr gr granoblastic arg'd & later silicified qtz-fspar (diatexite?) rock to 636.8m w/quartz-healed faults/breccia; cataclastic fault from 638.8-653.9m; tr to weak graphitic GnPel to EOH at 711m. Mineralized breccia from 629.1-629.3m (0.1 m at 0.06% eU from 601.9-602m and 0.7m at 0.17%eU from 628.9-629.6m using a cut-off of 0.05% for a total GT of 1.28).

HolePurposeComment: To test the up-dip expression of the graphitic cataclasite; weak mineralization and graphitic pelite intersected at depth in WC-492 at the unconformity along the Cigar North conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Str blching in the sst to 222.5 m becoming wk to mod to 502.4 m. Mod to str blch is intersected b/w 502.4 - 521.4 m and mod to nil from 521.4 m to the UC.Sst structure encountered from 117 to 124.2 m consists of steeply dipping fractures and rubble with mod dissol'n. From 179-205.1 m consists of intense fracturing and brecciation. Sharp UC at 555 m. Quartzo-feldspathic gneiss and intermittent pegmT was intersected from the UC to 578.4 m followed by alternating intervals of GranT and GnGran to the EOH at 651. Overall poor brittle structure in the bsmt; flt gouge and healed breccia at 576.7-578.4 m. NGRS peak of1742 cps is located at 578.7 m.

HolePurposeComment: To test the continuation of the brittle/ductile structure and weak mineralization along strike between the western edge of Phase 2 and WC-491.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 19.8 m. Wk toMod bl with intermittent diss zones in the upper sst.From 468 to 491.2 m the core is mod grey reduced. Faulting observed past 489 to the UC at 499.3 m. From 489.2 to 489.5m there is a 30cm fault gouge.Tr U-min between 491.2 and 493.0 m. Radiometry peak of 420cps assoc w/ tr frac hosted U-min.  Mod remob hem and lim alt observed within grey reduced sst.Sharp Uc at 499.3 m. Fn-gr chloritized GnPel to 505.7 m.Mod graphitic GnPel w/thin micro faults from 505.7 to the end of hole at 520. Cohesive cataclasite b/w 510.7 and 511m. Total GT 2.7; 3.4 m at 0.08 %eU from 482.3 to 495.4 m (.05 cut off) . Hole was lost due to drilling problems.

HolePurposeComment: To test a strong EM pick on L1400E along the Cigar North conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 21.0m. Sst has large intervals of alteration and structure. Unconformity at 528.85 m. Paleoweathering down to 582.2 m.From the unconformity to 625.1 m a fine to coarse grained dominantly granoblastic to weakly foliated diatexite and quartzo-feldspathic gneiss (where foliated) was intersected. Moderately argillized with patchy weak silicification. Trace graphitic clay occurs along fracture planes from 605.2 to 625.1 m. Strong alteration is intersected from 642.9 to 656.8 m. From 656.8 m a semi-fresh to fresh biotitic GnGran was intersected to the end of hole at 693 m. Brecciated intervals from 625.1- 631.7 m and 631.7-642.9 m. NGRS peak of 488.5 at 521.6 m.

HolePurposeComment: Test the extension of the graphitic package; location of the brittle/ductile structure; extension of umin and increased alteration to the north along section from the trace umin intersected in WC-494.
HoleGeneralComment: Hole Lost

HolePurposeComment: Test the extension of the graphitic package; location of the brittle/ductile structure; extension of umin and increased alteration to the north along section from the trace umin intersected in WC-494.
HoleGeneralComment: OB 19.2m. Sst was mod blchd with wk to mod lim to 210 m; mod to wk blch to the UC. Loc grey reduced intervals and zones of dissolution intermittently. Basal cgl is weakly bleached and competent with loc druzy quartz along fractures. Sst is poorly structured. White sandy clay gouge at 370.8 m. UC at 491.9 m. PWP is overprinted by mod chl. Upper bsmt has intermittent intervals of wk to mod chl and arg to 560 m past which it is dominantly fresh.The bsmt package consists primarily of graphitic GnPel. Weakly sheared cord bearing graphitic GnPel from 565-573.6m. Overall, the bsmt is poorly structured.Probe peak of 520 cps at 493m

HolePurposeComment: To test on section to the north from WC-494 for the continuation of mineralization and increased alteration to the north.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 19.0m. Upper sst strongly bleached to 42.8m; mod blch below followed by intervals of mod-wk bleaching throughout. Wkly blchd sections are often locally mod bleached. Greyish hue throughout some zones with highest intensity from 143.9-204m. Sst poorly structured. Increase in SPPY (70-90cps) in basal cgl followed by sharp UC at 465.3m & mod overprinted PWP consisting of green-red and green zones. Gamma peak of 220cps SPPY at 468.1m & probe peak of 1096cps in GnPel w/ hydrothermal hem & lim alt. Wkly graph cord augen gneiss from 512.4-542.1 & 565.3-572.5m. Otherwise weakly structured basement consists of variably graphitic GnPel.

HolePurposeComment: To fence WC-495 to the south, following up the strong sandstone structure at the unconformity and to test for the explanation to the strong EM pick on L1400E along the Cigar North conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Largely mod to str blchd sst with a few intervals in the upper/middle MFb with mod mottled purple hem. Lim in the upper sst. Grey reduced alt above the Uc. Loc wk desilic throughout assoc w/ structures. A few 10m rubbly/blocky structured zones thoughout the sst. Uc at 498.8 with narrow PWP wkly to mod'ly overprinted by blch in GnPsaPel. Upper bsmt consists of dom tr-wk graph GnPsaPel with many protocata-cataclastic flt/shear zones with mod remob graph. Lower bsmt consists of quartz flooded/vein/silicified granD with arg'd fspar followed by large interval of qtz-fspar rock interpreted to be diatexitic metased (psammite?).

HolePurposeComment: To test north of WC-489 to test for the western extenstion of the Cigar Main conductor and associated alteration and mineralization. WC-489 was interpreted to have intersected hanging-wall basement stratigraphy.
HoleGeneralComment: Sst was mod to loc str bleached throughout w/ loc intervals of weak bleaching. Sandy gouge at 530.6m w/ maroonish red remob hem over 10cm. Sst is otherwise poorly structured with most fractures being clean and open or minor desilic/argillization/pyrite. U/C at 538.4m is inferred due to local core loss w/ 50cm of wk to mod bleaching; PWP extends to 582.0m. Phlogopite bearing GnPel/GnPsaPel/GnPsa dominates the upper bsmt (541.1-619.3m); w/ variably graphitic GnPel below. Strongly graphitic cataclasite 628.1-632.9m. Weakly developed cord augen gneiss 666.4-675m (EOH). Probe peak 340cps in pegmT.

HolePurposeComment: To test the graphitic structure in WC-491 up-dip at the unconformity to test for the extension of mineralization and alteration.
HoleGeneralComment: Wk to mod blch to 302 m and mod to str blch below. Tr to mod S0 controlled/structure controlled/pervasive desilicification throughout sst. Mod to str argillization or massive clay replacement; hydrothermal hem; and limonite in the basal sst occurring both above & assoc w/ umin. Variable weak to strong umin below 440.1 metres to the Uc as diss to patchy black mineralization. Below Uc at 438.7 m narrow interval of mod argillized GnPel followed by a large interval of variably wk to str argillized pegmT with several dm- to m-scale layers of mod argillized and wk to mod chloritized fractured/brecciated GnPel with loc tr to wk diss graphite.

HolePurposeComment: Test the southern extent of graphitic package south of WC-333 and to test for source of anomalous Upartial in the lower sandstone of WC-333. Test the feasibility of the RC drilling for upper sandstone switching to NQ coring in the lower sandstone.
HoleGeneralComment: Casing to 28.95m. RC drilling to 201.5 (hole made water and hammer bit slowed down; at 184 m bit was switched to a tricone bit and RC continued to 201.5m before switching to NQ coring). MFb sandstone has diagenetic silicification and moderate diagenetic hematite stain; then becomes moderately to strongly bleached in the basal sandstone at 392m. Uc at 409.1m. PW metaseds to 433m with a local m-scale fracture/breccia/gouge zone. Competent chloritized phlogopite(?) psammo-pelitie to psammite below to becoming fresh and with abundant colourless/pale green splintery amphibole with depth to EOH. Local m-scale pegmatite throughout basement.

HolePurposeComment: To test between the Cigar Main and Cigar East pods to follow up on anomalous sandstone geochemistry (elevated illite and Upartial) and mineralization intersected at the unconformity in the area, Fencing WC-303 to the north.
HoleGeneralComment: RC drilling completed to 235.95m. Conventional hammer drilling with RC rig as a test to 317.7m returning the water/cutting outside the rods. NQ coring from 317.7m to end of hole at 504m. Regional MFb becoming mod to str bleached in basal sst. Uc at 453.1m. Structured interval from 439 to Uc with wk patchy Umin amongst elevated sst. Common clay gge/flt intervals (often hosting Umin) bounding blocks of comp sst often with rotated bedding. 3-4 ~10cm blocks of bsmt(?) in sst with faulted contacts. Grey reduced above Uc. Assoc hydro hem and lim with Umin. Bsmt is fn-med gr wk to mod graphitic GnPel loc w/ augen cord texture w/ cord up to 1cm. Wk Umin in frac and gge in bsmt close to Uc. Wk blch and mod chl in bsmt. Total GT of 12.4896 using cut off of 0.05%eU over 7.4m at 0.017%eU.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting mineralization at the unconformity approximately 150m along strike to the east from WC-500 where the graphitic package is interpreted to subcrop at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Drill holes was lost at 483m when the rods became stuck. Attempted to wedge off to complete the drill hole but sand was flowing into the hole and prevented being able to set the plug.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test along strike of the mineralization intersected in WC-500. WC-503A is targeting the sub crop of the structured graphitic pelitic gneiss at the unconformity approximately 150 metre along strike to the east.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately bleached MFc. Weakly to moderately bleached MFb. M-scale fracture zones with weak to moderate desilicification throughout sandstone. Strong bleaching below 454.5 m. Trace to weak Umin in basal sandstone from 488.6 to 496.9 m consisting of fracture controlled mineralization in an upper desilicifed zone to disseminated along bedding in a lower silicified zone; moderate to strong grey reduced alteration. Basement dominantly fine-grained pelitic to interlayered psammo-pelitic gneiss. Variable graphite weak to moderate and decreasing with depth. Cataclastic faulting from 501.6-505.9 m.

HolePurposeComment: Test the extent of mineralization west of pase two. Wedge hole from WC-503A to test for additional higher grade mineralization south of the u/c intercept of WC-503A. Wedge set at 297m in WC-503A to create offcut.
HoleGeneralComment: Strong alteration from 480 m to uc(495.8m): trace U-min; grey reduced; hydrothermal hematite; desilicification; and argillization.  Intervals of trace to weak U-min from 482.9 to 483.9 m, 486.1 to 489.1 m, and 490.4 to 493.7 m. Locally associated with blocky/fracture intervals and commonly as disseminated mineralization parallel to bedding within competent sandstone. Basement consists of variably graphitic pelite - moderately graphitic from 510.5 to 520 m with local proto-cataclastic to cataclastic deformation. Using a cut-off of 0.05%, WC-503A-1 intersected 10 m at 0.14% from 482.5 to 495.6 m for a GT of 13.6.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test the unconformity 65 metres to the south of WC-492. Following up on anomalous Upartial thoughout the lower sandstone and large several metre-scale breccia intervals interpreted to be rooted in the basement to the south.
HoleGeneralComment: Mod-str bl from OB to 179m; wk-mod to 487m; mod from 487m to 510.5m. Uc @ 511.6m. Brittle flt zone breccia in sst from 325.2-327.4m: Mod arg; sst clasts; slt matrix. Damage zones above/below. Rubbly incohesive zone from 486.2 to 511.6m. Grey-reduced from 501-510.5m. Bsmt is metatexite to 533m; followed by >10% graph cataclasite @ 550.7-578.5 and 581.5-605.5m. Both contain str arg; str chl; mod py. Str bl and arg flt zone @ 609.5-615.3m: Interval is brecciated qtz-cl gouge. Alternating psapel and psammitic gneisses and diatexites below to the EOH at 714.7m. Tr to loc mod graph + py.  SppY peak of 220cps in 2cm qtz vein at 679.4m. NGRS peak of 1121 cps in the basal sandstone at 499.6 m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing for mineralization at the Uc 17.5 metres south of WC-494 which intersected several elevated faults and broadly anomalous geochemistry in the basal 20 metres of sandstone - west along strike from Phase 2.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 8m. Poorly altered sandstone until 433m followed by moderately bleached sandstone to UC. Trace mineralization is intersected in the lower sandstone ?just above the basal conglomerate unit. Altered UC at 483.1. Entire bsmt package is variably graphitic pelitic to psammo-pelitc gneiss. Intersected 2.1 m at 0.21 %eU from 472 to 478.1 m for a GT of 1.53 using a cut-off of 0.05 %. End of hole at 582 m.

HolePurposeComment: Determine extent of mineralization west of phase two.
HoleGeneralComment: Ob to 5 m; poor sst alteration until 444m. Faulting with trace mineralization between 468 and 470.4 m. UC at 470.4 m ? the depth is estimated due to core loss. Basement is dominantly graphitic pelite, one interval of non graphitic psammitic gneiss. EOH at 579m. WC-506 intersected 3.9 m at 0.21 %eU from 456.6 to 474.5m with a max grade of 1.19% from 470.3-470.4 m using a cut-off of 0.05 %.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted south of WC-498; appoximately 11m of mineralization was intersectd within the basal sandstone.
HoleGeneralComment: Strongly to moderately bleached MFc. Weakly to locally moderately bleached MFb. Local trace to moderate desilicification throughout sandstone, commonly associated with increased fracture zones. Trace to moderate Umin in basal sandstone from 473 to 488.1m disseminated along bedding and locally fracture controlled; moderate to strong grey reduced alteration. Basement dominantly fine-grained pelitic gneiss to local psammo-pelitic lenses. Variable graphite trace to moderate decreasing below 592.4m. Protocataclastic and cataclastic faulting noted 551.9 to 579.8 and 615.5 to 622.9m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the up-dip expression of graphitic faulting intersected at depth in WC-506 approximately 60 m north at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 5 m; str bl to 42m and from 454-476.5m. Rubbly bl and desil intervals from 445.5-454 and 468-474m. Uc @ 493.4m: str arg and remob hem to 495m. GnGraPel GnPel; and GnPsaPel dominant in bsmt. Graphite content of pelitic gneisses: 5-10% from 504.2-515.3m; 1-5% from 519.3-526 m; 534-559.4 m; and 560.4-570 m. Trace elsewhere. Protocataclasite from 519.8-520m. Isoclinal folding and contorted S1 from 564 to 570 m. Shear zone from 542-546 m. SppY max: 120 cps. Probe peak: 1401 cps in pwp bsmt @494.3 m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the unconformity 15 meters to the north of WC-507 where the brittle faulting intersected at depth in WC-507 is interpreted to have offset the unconformity between WC-507 and WC-498. Testing for an extension of the mineralization intersected in WC-507 to the north associated with the nose of the offset.
HoleGeneralComment: Strongly to moderately bleached MFc. Weakly to locally moderately bleached MFb. Local trace to weak desilicification throughout sandstone commonly associated with increased fracture zones. Trace to very locally weak Umin in basal sandstone from 488 to 499 m disseminated along bedding and locally structurally controlled; moderate to weak grey reduced alteration. Basement dominantly fine-grained pelitic gneiss with local diatexite intervals. Variable graphite trace to moderate decreasing below 564 m. Protocataclastic and cataclastic faulting noted 520.1-530.1, 540.1-544.4, 557-564, and 567-573m. Probe peak 38085 cps at 496.0m.

HolePurposeComment: Determine extent of mineralization west of phase two.
HoleGeneralComment: Hole was restarted due to deviation in dip.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the up-dip expression of an altered and reactivated graphitic fault intersected at depth in WC-499 (2016 drill hole) approximately 75 m north at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone was weakly to moderately bleached throughout with moderate to strong bleaching below 370m to Uc. Moderate to strong desilicification 447-456m. Uc 463.2m. Massive clay interval from 463.2-464.6m. Fault breccia with argillized matrix and angular clasts up to 5mm noted to 469.6m. Fine to medium-grained pelitic gneiss from 469.6 to 472 and 480-482.2m. Weak to moderately graphitic pelitic gneiss 472-480m. From 482.2 to the EOH at 681m, argillized and chloritized pegmatite was encountered. A probe peak of 2056.25 cps at 464.5m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the down-dip extension of the sandstone structures and elevated uranium partial in WC-492 at the unconformity in between the unconformity intersections of WC-492 and WC-504 approximately 35 metres away at the unconformity. Testing for an extension of the mineralization intersected in WC-507 400m to the west on the same unconformity step.
HoleGeneralComment: WC-511. Strongly to moderate bleached MFc. Weak to locally moderate bleached MFb. Local weak desilicification throughout sandstone commonly associated with increased fracturing. Weak to moderate reduced grey from 485 to Uc at 519.7m. Graphitic pelitic gneiss 540.3-554m with weak to moderate graphite. Remainder of basement dominantly diatexite pelitic gneiss with local gneissic intervals. Protocataclastic and cataclastic faulting noted 540.3-554.0m. Numerous intervals of Umin of varying degrees: 552.2-552.8 (wk-mod), 563.8-564 (mod), 564.5-564.8 (str), 592.6-593.2 (tr-wk), 642.9-644.9 m (tr). Probe peak 58090cps at 564.6m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing L18E along the Cigar North conductor; 400m east along strike of the mineralization intersected in WC-507.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately to strongly bleached MFc with common early healed micro-faulting/deformation bands with local intervals of fractured/reactivated structures. Generally weakly to locally strongly bleached MFb associated with fracture zones, local reactivated early micro-faulting/deformation bands, and moderate silicification. Uc at 495.8m. Variably graphitic (trace to weak) pelitic gneiss down to 571m followed by moderately silicified/quartz-flooded quartzofeldspathic gneiss, interpreted as diatexite, to the EOH at 618m. Local cataclastic to ultracataclastic faulting from 569.9-571m. Probe peak of 3005 cps at 494.7m. Using a cut-off of 0.05%eU, WC-512 intersected 0.3m at 0.06%eU from 494.8-495.6m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the unconformity 200m along strike to the west from WC-500 testing for an extension to the mineralization along strike. Targeting the subcrop of the graphitic brittle/ductile structure at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Tr-wk bl in MFc, alternating wk and mod bl in MFb. Small rubbly desil zones from 371-377 and 379-680m. Rubbly desil for 30m above Uc. Mod grey-reduced zone 1m above Uc. Str cl replacement above Uc, 5 metres of str cl replacement and remob hem 5m below Uc into bsmt. Tr-wk Umin in altered basal sst at 455.7m. Fgr wk-graph gnpel from 473.6-484.6 and again from 490.5-498.6m. Rest of hole alternates btw fgr gnpel and pegmt/diatexitic gneisses with rare graphite and wk-mod diss py. Probe peak of 20,312 cps at 456 metres.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test the unconformity 50m to the north of the unconformity intersection in WC-512; testing the up-dip projection of the brittle reactivation within the cataclasite structures in the basement of WC-512.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately to strongly bleached MFc. Weakly bleached MFb. Large structured interval 443.9-469.2 m consisting of early cohesive breccia surrounding large in-cohesive fault gouge with moderate to strong desilicification and argillization; abundant core loss. Uc 524.9m; sharp. Typical PWP down to 577.9m. Variably anatectic quartzofeldspathic gneiss to 577.9m. Quartz breccia with local strong to complete replacement of host rock down to 590.4m. Altered diatexite with minor quartz flooding to 595.1m. Below 595.1 to EOH at 626.4m granitic gneiss was intersected; very siliceous with local quartz veining, abundant k-spar, and local granodiorite. Generally competent basement with local increased fracturing and minor faulting. Probe peak of 758.23 cps at 555.0 m within paleoweathered diatexite gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: Following up weak U-min encounted at the UC in WC-513 as well the the up dip expression of faulting in WC-513.
HoleGeneralComment: Weak to moderate bleaching below 87 m to Uc at 448.1m. 369.3-387m: blocky with high angled fractures and variable desilicification. Paleoweathered pelitic gneiss to 449.6m. Bleached pegmatite to 451.5m. Weakly graphitic pelitic gneiss with minor local intervals of trace mineralization noted to 478.8. Remainder of basement psammite to moderately graphitic pelite. Increase in ductile deformation closer to EOH due to lithology contrast between regionally structured pegmatite starting at 497.8m. Probing peak with NGRS of 4530cps at 455.6m. Using a cut-off of 0.05%eU, intersected 1.5m at 0.08%eU for total GT of 1.2.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test the unconformity expression of the mineralized brittle structure intersected in the basement of WC-511 and down-dip of the sandstone structure and elevated geochemistry in WC-492. Targeting the 30m step at the unconformity; approximately 25m north of the uc in WC-511.
HoleGeneralComment: Intense alteration and structure throughout the majority of the sandstone column. Hole was lost in structured quartz dissolution zone at 308.2m. Attempting to hit the same target in WC-518.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting a resistivity sandstone breach and elevated U-partial vectoring North of WC-448.
HoleGeneralComment: Weakly bleached throughout majority of sandstone with local strongly bleached intervals. Regional structure throughout with infrequent fractures and rare desilicified zones. Basal conglomerate 372.3 to Uc with hydrothermal hematite staining, increased heavy mineral banding, and minor increased radiometry. Minor deformation consisting of fracturing and blocky/desilicified sections. Uc 388.8m. Paleoweathered metatexite pelitic gneiss to 397.3m. Graphitic pelitic gneiss to 414.9m. Pelitic gneiss to 430.2m. Remainder of basement moderate to strongly graphitic pelitic gneiss with minor pelite towards EOH. Local protocataclasite and brecciation. Probe peak of 1081.67 cps in the basal sandstone at 315.3 metres.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the same planned unconformity intersection as WC-516 as an angled drill hole to avoid the drilling difficulties associated with drilling vertical down the structure. Targeted to test the unconformity expression of the mineralized brittle structure intersected in the basement of WC-511 and down-dip of the sandstone structure and elevated geochemistry in WC-492. Targeting the 30 metres step at the unconformity; approximately 25 metres north of the unconformity in WC-511.
HoleGeneralComment: Sandstone with moderate to weak bleaching and intermittent intervals of pervasive silicification, grey reduction, argillization; faulting between 322-325 m and 423-440m. Unconformities at 496.4m and 528.4m. Primary basement lithology is quartz-rich diatexite. Basement mineralization was intersected between 554.9-561.3m, 585.8-587m,  and 597-599m, and is dominantly fracture controlled. Using a cut-off of 0.05%, WC-518 intersected 11.5m at 0.18% for a total GT of 20.84, discontinuous from 554.6 to 599.3 m. 20cm at 1.13% at 560.7m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted approx 65m south of WC-512 at the u/c testing the hanging-wall step in the unconformity along strike to the east of the mineralization intersected in WC-507. Testing down-dip of the sandstone structures (quartz flooded structures and open fractures) intersected in the upper and middle sandstone of WC-512.
HoleGeneralComment: Strongly to moderately bleached MFc. Weak to locally strongly bleached MFb. Local trace to weak desilicification throughout sandstone commonly associated with increased fracturing. Fault zone displaying abundant core loss, desilicification, local silicification, local clay, and rare rotated bedding was noted 402-420.5m. Uc at 476.3m; rubbly. Basement dominantly fine to medium-grained variably graphitic (trace to moderate) pelitic gneiss to 583.4m. From 583.4 to EOH at 605m, fine-grained gneiss (pelite/psammo-pelite/calc-pelite?) was intersected with weak to moderate chlorite and trace to moderate silicification. Protocataclastic and cataclastic faulting noted 551.8-570.2; 578.8-583.4; 595.3-595.5m. Probe peak 598.33cps at 484.9m.

HolePurposeComment: Initial test of a moderate conductor pick on line 2+00E. 800 metres to the west of basement mineralization intersected on line 10+00E and 400 metres to the west of CIG-203 that intersected variably graphitic pelitic gneiss with cataclastic deformation.
HoleGeneralComment: Drill hole became stuck at 86.8 m while pulling rods. Casing was initially reamed down to 33 m. First box received consisted of blocky sub-crop with mixed erratic boulders; sandstone/basement starting in the next box at 32.5 m. It is assumed that depth of casing was insufficient allowing the rods to get sanded in. Rods were cut above core barrel and salvaged.

HolePurposeComment: Step back 5 feet from lost drill hole WC-520; initial test of a moderate conductor pick on line 2+00E; 800 metres to the west of basement mineralization intersected on line 10+00E and 400 metres to the west of CIG-203 that intersected variably graphitic pelitic gneiss with cataclastic deformation.
HoleGeneralComment: Strongly to moderately bleached MFc. Weak to locally strongly bleached MFb. Moderately structured interval displaying rubbly/blocky core and local sand from 485.5-490.5m. Uc at 555.0m; rubbly. To 641.5 m basement dominantly diatexite with local psammo-pelite (561.2-565.5m) and trace to moderate graphitic pelitic gneiss (565.5-574.2m). To EOH at 681.3m alternating intervals of amphibole rich mafic gneiss and pelitic gneiss were intersected. Numerous structure zones: 565.5-580.1m: protocataclasite with local cataclasite and rare ultracataclasite; 583.3-585.5m: ultracataclasite. 587.3-590.0m: cataclasite with local protocataclasite. 590.0-592.6m: matrix supported clay gouge. Probe peak 618.841cps at 318.3m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the unconformity approximately 20 metres south of the mineralization intersected in WC-507; testing for the southern limit to the mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately to locally bleached MFC, weak towards MFb. Local limonite below 73m. 214.1-238.5m: structured interval with protobreccia and 1cm gouge. Fracture corridor from 361.8-379m: local sandy clay gouge and weak drusy quartz. Unconformity at 481.3m: sharp 70 dtca contact between competent grey-reduced basal sandstone and metasediments. Fine grained psammopelitic and psammitic gneiss to 536.9m. Well-preserved paleoweathering to 505.9m. Local trace graphite below 523m, trace to moderate within a cordierite-bearing metatexitic pelitic gneiss to end of hole at 554.8 metres. Abundant breccia/gouge below the unconformity; several 5-10cm cataclasitic faults near graphitic pelitic gneiss interval. Probe peak: 579cps at 502.6m in PWP psammopelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: Initial test of a weak conductor pick on line 6+00W; 800 metres to the west of WC-520A and representing the furthest west drill hole in the Cigar North area to date.
HoleGeneralComment: Upper sandstone moderately to strongly bleached,  MFb regionally altered. Two minor faults intersected in sandstone.  Sharp UC at 533.2 m, followed by paleoweathered pelitic gneiss. Trace to weak disseminated graphite within psammopeltic to pelitic gneiss until approximately 638 m, after which graphite content increases to moderate to locally massive. Significant structure is intersected in the basement. Reactivated shear zones as well as graphitic cataclasites between 575-584m,  645.5-648.5m,  660.8-661.8m, 704-709m, and 739-747m. Diatexite unit at 747.5 m to EOH. NGRS probe peak of 375.71 cps at 532.4m just above the unconformity in blocky regional basal conglomerate.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the unconformity 90 metres north of CIG-203 which was interpreted to be hanging-wall to the main cataclasite structures. Targeted to test the strong EM pick on line L6+00E.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderate to locally strongly bleached MFc. Weak to locally moderately bleached MFb. Breccia noted from 344.7-349 m, with damage zones from 323.5-344.7m and 349.0-406.0m, displaying blocky/rubbly core with moderate to weak desilicification and local trace to weak clay. Uc at 520.8m. Diatexite noted to 525.3m. From 525.3-527.5m: fine-grained chert-like ultracataclasite. Basement dominantly granitic gneiss with weak to moderate chlorite and argillization. Quartz flooding noted from 581.3-583.7m. Local micro-fracturing noted throughout basement, commonly infilled with chlorite and clay. Remnant PWP to 551m. Probe peak of 1088.517 cps at 542.9m. *Run block shift of 3m deeper from 413 to 522m; correct from OB to 413 and 525 to EOH.*

HolePurposeComment: Fencing CIG-212 to the northwest; following up the anomalous sandstone geochemistry and altered calc-silicate basement. Approximately 200m along strike to the southwest from the unconformity mineralization intersected in WC-507.
HoleGeneralComment: Upper sandstone moderately to strong bleached until 200 m, poor alteration until 406.5 m, increase in alteration past 465 m including moderate bleaching, intermittent weak to moderate argillization, local grey reduced, and local structurally controlled dissolution. Altered unconformity at 471.6 m. PWP  overprinted by bleaching and weak remobilized hematite. Basement is poorly structured; upper basement lithology comprised of calcsilicate/psammopelite until 531 m, followed by graphitic pelitic gneiss and anatectic pegmatite to end of hole at 584.6m.  NGRS probe peak of 1142 cps at 472.2 m just below the unconformity.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test the unconformity 30 m to the northwest of WC-524 testing the subcrop contact between the calc-bearing psammo-pelitic gneiss and the graphitic pelitic gneiss along strike from WC-507. Following up on the anomalous alteration intersected in the lower sandstone and upper basement of WC-524.
HoleGeneralComment: Weak to moderate bleaching through the sandstone. Sandstone faulting is intersected from 401 to 416 m. UC at 480.8 m. The upper basement lithology is comprised of variable psammopelitic gneiss until 522.5 m. From 522.5 m to the end of hole at 626.2 m the basement lithology is dominantly variably graphitic locally cordierite bearing pelitic to psammopelitic gneiss. Common meter scale zones of anatectic pegmatite intersected throughout. Significant basement structure was intersected including graphitic cataclasite between 607.1- 609.3 and 618.3 to 619.4 m. NGRS probe peak of 1062 cps at 533.7 m within sheared graphitic pelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test the unconformity 100m south of WC-520A which is interpreted to be footwall to the main structure and mineralization along strike to the east in WC-511 and WC-518.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderate to strongly bleached MFc. Weak to locally moderately bleached MFb. Sandstone generally poorly structured. Local increased fracturing with associated trace to weak desilicification and druzy quartz. Unconformity at 557.3m; rubbly. Fine-grained pelitic gneiss noted to 573m. Remainder of basement dominantly fine to medium-grained variably graphitic (trace to moderate) pelitic gneiss. Weakly bleached pegmatite noted from 663.6-667.4m. Protocataclastic and cataclastic faulting noted from 618-625.1m, 643.9-649m, and 667.4-677m. Probe peak of 375 cps at 556.3m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test approximately 80 m south of unconformity of WC-504 on L1000E testing along the interpreted structural strike associated with the mineralization intersected in WC-507. The drill hole is also targeted to test down-dip of the basement along the section including the elevated uranium partial in the graphitic pelitic gneiss and down-dip of the mineralized vertical basement structure in WC-511 and WC-518.
HoleGeneralComment: Wedge at 269.2m. Moderately bleached MFc. Generally weakly bleached MFb with moderate bleaching and weak to strong grey-reduced alteration noted 402.6-461.3m. Numerous structural intervals: 426-427.9m: protobreccia to breccia; 427.9-428.5m: clay gouge; 455.8-456.4m: clay gouge/clay replacement. Uc at 515.1 m. Basement composed of metatexite psammo-pelitic to pelitic gneiss with abundant m-scale quartzofeldspathic leucosome to 747.1 m followed by granite to EOH. Variable graphite from trace to moderate disseminated and remobilized graphite. Numerous zones of protocataclastic to cataclastic faulting noted: 657.4-730.1m; 730.1-743.9m with large quartz breccia. Cataclastic to ultracataclastic faulting 743.9-750.55m. Probe peak 952.9 cps at 559.7m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test L1400E along strike from the mineralized basement structure intersected on L1000E. Targeted in between the unconformity intercepts of WC-498 and WC-495 down dip of the sandstone structure intersected in the middle sandstone of WC-495. Testing the down dip extension of the basement structure at the unconformity and in the basement within the diatextite unit.
HoleGeneralComment: Drill hole left open and casing in and capped. Moderate to locally strongly bleached MFc. Weak to locally moderately bleached MFb. Sandstone displayed trace to weak deformation throughout with local zones of faulting. 325.5-341m: proto-brecciated to brecciated sandstone with local rubbly zones and trace to weak desilicification; 407.6-450.2m: blocky interval with sand and local gouge; common silica healed fractures throughout. Uc 515.8 @ 75dtca. Diatexite to EOH at 611.6m; weak to moderate bleaching; and trace to weak silicification locally. Blocky 569-574.5m; 588.0-599.0m. Very trace disseminated graphite and pyrite locally. Probe peak 1078 cps at 548.4m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting northwest of WC-525; the subcrop of the contact between the graphitic metasediments and hanging-wall calcsilicate/psammite. Testing for unconformity mineralization along strike of WC-507.
HoleGeneralComment: Overall the sandstone column has weak to locally moderate bleaching and  minor dissolution. Fracture interval associated with moderate bleaching between 350-390 m. Basement consists of variably graphitic pelitic metatexite. Well-developed PWP. Upper basement was poorly altered - alteration increases with depth with weak to locally moderate chlorite and argillization. Common thin cohesive cataclasites in lower basement with only minor reactivation. Local weak to moderate shearing. NGRS probe peak of 828.75cps @ 563.5 m within anatectic granite.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the 125 m gap along strike from the western edge of the Phase 2 pod and the next historical drill fence which had trace mineralization. Testing 60 m along strike; targeting the southern edge of the graphitic pelitic gneiss directly along strike of the mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: Weak to moderately bleached MFc. Moderate to weakly bleached MFb. Local trace to weak desilicification associated with densely fractured zones. Trace to strong Umin in basal sandstone from 452.6 to 458.7 m and extending into basement to 458.8 m: disseminated along bedding and locally structured controlled; moderate grey reduced alteration. Basement dominantly fine to medium-grained metatexite pelitic gneiss with local intervals of pelitic gneiss. Variable graphite: trace to moderate disseminated and remobilized. Common anatectic granites throughout. Protocataclastic and cataclastic faulting noted: 496.2-503.7; 506.7-513.1; and 564.2-566.3 m. Probe peak of 54925 cps at 457.6 m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the unconformity 20 m north of the intercept in WC-530 for an extension of the mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: Weak to moderately bleached MFc. Moderately bleached MFb. Local zones of gouge and blocky core associated with zones of desilicification from 381-462.8 m. Uc at 462.8 m ? altered and structured; soft clay gouge 462.8-463.3 m with 30 dtca contacts. From 462.8 to 474 m: diatexitic pelitic gneiss. From 474-506.3 m: metatexitic pelitic gneiss with moderate to locally strong disseminated and remobilized graphite. From 506.3-521.5 m: mixed zone of metatexitic pelitic gneiss and very fine-grained anatectic pelitic gneiss. From 521.5 to EOH (573 m): fine-grained weak to trace graphitic pelitic gneiss. Protocataclastic and cataclastic faulting noted from 497.2-506.3 m. Local anatectic granites (largest interval from 533.5-535.8 m). Probe peak of 2671.65 cps at 460.9 m in basal sandstone.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the 55 m gap at the unconformity between WC-303 and WC-295. Following up the anomalous Upartial and illite throughout much of the sandstone column and testing for mineralization at the unconformity.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderate bleaching to 225 m; primary hematite from 225-368 m; followed by moderate bleaching. Local weak limonite for upper 25 m of sst; weak from 104-148 m. Druzy quartz and black oxide coatings; occasional sooty pyrite. Poorly structured sandstone; short interval of weak to moderate dissolution in basal sst. Uc at 454.7 m. Fine and medium-grained pelitic gneiss with disseminated pyrite throughout basement. Short paleoweathering profile. Trace graphite intermittently. Weakly graphitic pelitic gneiss from 498.8 -515.4 m. Patchy weak bleaching down to 488.5 m; moderate bleaching to 498.5 m. Pelitic gneiss from 531.5 to 538.7 m: several brittle-ductile shears within unit (531.6-531.8, 532.2-532.7, and 538.1-538.4 m). Foliation at 30-40 dtca. Shears at 20-30 dtca. Probing peak of 543 cps in basal sandstone at 439 m.

HolePurposeComment: Wedge hole off of WC-533 at 226 m; targeting 100 m east-southeast along strike of the main offsetting structure and basement mineralization in WC-511 and WC-518. Testing the sandstone structure intersected in WC-533 down-dip in the basement.
HoleGeneralComment: Weakly bleached to 355.5 m; moderate to strong to the Uc at 502.85 m. Fractured zones with local moderate desilicification and grey-reduced from 355.5-381 m and 467.4-500.6 m. Hanging wall pelitic gneiss from Uc to 572.4 m. PWP to 523.5 m. Variable trace to moderate disseminated and remobilized graphite below; common protocataclastic fabric below 529.4 m; and larger cataclastic to ultracataclastic faulting below 553.6 m. Weakly mineralized interval at the base of the hanging wall over 20cm in weakly argillized ultracataclasite with 750-925cps. Footwall granite/granitic gneiss below 572.4 m. Large cataclasite/ultracataclasite from 572.4-580.3 m and 660.9-669.7 m. Quartz breccia/quartz flooded intervals peripheral to faulting from 580.3-592 m; 647.9-660.9 m; and 669.7-687 m. Moderate muddy-green alteration/quartz flooding/cataclastic fabric overprinting primary texture. Brittle fracture zones with local breccia from 626.5-637.3 m and 649.7-662.7 m. EOH in fresh granitic gneiss at 701.4 m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting 100 m east-southeast along the interpreted strike of the basement mineralization in WC-511 and WC-518.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 32.1 m. Sandstone bleaching and argillization along with common zones of weak to moderate fracturing; faulting; and local core loss occur between 345 and 502 m. Main fault core (clay gouge zones) occurs between 360.8-360.7; 441.7-445.0; 468.7-470.5 and 491-495 m with local rotated bedding. Medium to fine-grained granitic gneiss was intersected from the unconformity at 517.7 to 685.9 m; common breccia zones from 563 to 567; 600.4 to 602.4; 653.7 to 656.5; and 668.9 to 670.2 m. Overall moderate to strong alteration throughout the basement. Metasediments intersected from 685.9 to end of hole at 707.4 m including cataclasite intervals with local reactivation. Probe peak of 1291.7 cps in granitic gneiss at 601.3 m proximal to chloritic clay gouge.

HolePurposeComment: Vertical drill hole testing the unconformity ~12 m south of the WC-530 unconformity intercept. Testing for possible extension of unconformity mineralization intersected in WC-530.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderate to weakly bleached MFc. Moderate to locally weakly bleached MFb. Local zones of gouge and blocky core associated with zones of desilicification from 401.7-448.7 m. Uc at 448.7 m ? altered ~ 75 dtca. From 448.7-458.2 m: anatectic pelitic gneiss with remnant weak PWP and weak bleaching overprinting. From 458.2-485.8 m: anatectic pelitic gneiss with trace to rarely weak disseminated graphite. From 485.8 to EOH (518.2 m): medium-grained anatectic graphitic pelitic gneiss displaying moderate to weak disseminated and remobilized graphite. Trace ductile deformation with cordierites with poorly developed augen texture. Two thin quartz/carbonate breccias from 463.6-464.1 and 465.6-465.7 m. Local anatectic granites (largest interval from 478.6-480.2 m). Probe peak of 1055.7 cps at 448.6 m in basal sandstone.

HolePurposeComment: Wedge hole to get past stuck core barrel at the bottom of WC-535. Testing the EM pick on L8600E onthe Contact conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Strongly bleached MFc. Weakly bleached MFb. Local weak to moderately silicified weak fracture interval from 316-324m. Blocky dissolution zone for 50m above Uc. Uc at 403.3m - sharp contact at 75 dtca. Variably anatectic fine to medium-grained pelitic gneiss below. Weakly graphitic from 429.4-447.3m. 447.3-452.8m: protocataclasite in fine-grained pelitic gneiss ? moderate remobilized graphite in shear/fault planes. Sheared pelitic gneiss from 525.7-533.7m with several short protocataclasite intervals (moderate remobilized graphite and pyrite stringers/vein fill). Foliated calc-silicate from 539.5-543.9m intercalated with pelitic material. Psammo-pelitic gneiss (trace graphite) to 555.4m; alkali feldspar pegmatite with pelite rafts to EOH at 560.5m. Probing peak of 1617 cps in a pegmatite at 495.3m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the 2012 moving loop EM pick on line 8600E along the Contact conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: Rods became stuck and the hole was abandoned.

HolePurposeComment: Testing 130 m north of the unconformity intercept of 2017 drill hole WC-522. Targeting the subcrop of the graphitic cataclasite and quartz-breccia at the unconformity and into the basement. Interpreted to represent the main unconformity-offsetting structure that is mineralized approximately 1.5 km along strike to the east-southeast.
HoleGeneralComment: Weak to locally moderately bleached MFc. Weak to locally moderately bleached MFb. Local blocky zones associated with trace to moderate desilicification: 478.3-485.5; 495.5-500.6; and 517.9-521.0 m. Uc 551.4 m: rubbly. PWP pelitic gneiss to 566.1 m. Graphitic pelitic gneiss to 583.7 m. Granitic gneiss to EOH at 683.5 m; weak to moderate bleaching noted to 625.8 m and weak argillization to 662.7 m; fresh below 664.9 m. Local zones of brittle faulting: 564.1-567.8; 567.8-569; 583.7-585.6; 585.6-586; 625.5-625.8; and 638.6-646.9 m. Probe peak of 968.8 cps at 549.1 m in basal sandstone.

HolePurposeComment: Wedge hole off of WC-537 when the core barrel broke off. Testing the 2012 Moving Loop EM pick on line 12000E; proximal to an interpreted flexure in the magnetic data and potential cross-cutting; NNW trending lineament.
HoleGeneralComment: **All data shifted 3m shallower from 257 m to the EOH** Strong quartz dissolution between 251 and 284 m with small intervals of complete core loss. Moderate to locally strongly bleached MFc associated with strongly desilicified zones. Minor mineralization which appeared to be fracture controlled from 396.3 to 396.4 m - probing peak of 3450 cps. Weakly bleached zone directly below the unconformity at 383.7 m followed by a strong PWP to 404.2 m. Weakly structured throughout basement. Weak graphite content to 442.8 m followed by trace graphite through the rest of the hole with the graphite being associated with fractures. Small intervals of calc-silicate banding and anatectic melt among pelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: Targeted to test the 2012 Moving Loop EM pick on L12000E along the Contact conductor; proximal to an interpreted cross-cutting magnetic lineament and break in the northeast trending magnetic high to the north of the interpreted northeast trending conductor trend.
HoleGeneralComment: Core tube became stuck at 275.5m (that core was not recovered); when rods were pulled out to retrieve the stuck tube the rod string broke at the adapter coupling just below the locking coupler and left the core barrel and tube at the bottom of the hole. It could not be retrieved. First wedge attempt was at 221.5m but the wedge sheared off 11metres above the plug. Second attempt at 198.6m was successful - drill hole proceeded as WC-537-1.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the 2018 Moving Loop EM pick on L1300W on the Cigar North grid.
HoleGeneralComment: Weakly bleached MFc. Weak to rarely moderately bleached MFb. Uc at 552 m at 80 dtca. PWP pelitic gneiss to 585.7 m. Trace graphite pelitic gneiss to 605.9 m. Weak to moderately graphitic pelitic gneiss to 614.7 m. Anatectic granite to 618.9 m. Metatexite pelitic gneiss to 630 m. From 630 to 693.8 m: variably graphitic pelitic gneiss. From 693.8-716.7 and 731.5-779 m: medium-grained granitic gneiss; muddy green alteration to 767.7 m; fresh to 775.3 m. Quartz breccia from 716.7 to 731.5 m. Abundant faulting throughout basement: 605-614.5; 632.7-633.1; 635-639.8; 651.7-656; 686.6-693.8; 713.1-714.2; and 775.3-779 m; common weak structure between. Probe peak of 547.83 cps at 551.4 m in basal sandstone.

HolePurposeComment: Wedge hole off of WC-539 at 347 metres to the north. Testing for an extension of unconformity mineralization intersected in WC-539 to the north at the fault nose. Additionally testing for an up dip expression of the mineralization intersected at depth in WC-539 along the main thrust fault where it projects up the unconformity at the sandstone wedge.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately to strongly bleached MFb sandstone with trace pyrite/druzy quartz on a few fractures and grey-reduced alteration in the basal sandstone. Below 472 m: moderately to strongly fractured with weak to moderate silicification. Uc at 501.5 m with silicified altered basement below before intersecting main offsetting thrust fault as a m-scale clay gouge with moderate chlorite/hydrothermal hematite. Below main fault a sandstone wedge was intersected with a second Uc at 523.8 m. Trace Umin associated with hydrothermal hematite and chlorite in fractures/S0 in lower half of sandstone wedge and extending into strongly fractured/grey-reduced basement directly below second Uc. The rest of the basement consisted of moderately to strongly silicified footwall granite to 561 m followed by a narrow interval of persevered PWP then moderately muddy-green altered footwall granite to the end of the hole at 496.4 m. Probing peak of 8000 cps at 524 m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing for the extension of basement mineralization approximately 100 m to the west of intersection in WC-511 and WC-518.
HoleGeneralComment: Grey reduced sandstone past 383 m; several narrow fault intervals in the basal sandstone. Umin straddles the unconformity and is intersected within the basement. Moderate pitchblende is observed from 499.6-501.2 m; unconformity contact at 499.9 m. Abundant structure-controlled Umin from 531.4-535.8 m spanning over the contact between hanging-wall cataclasite and gouged footwall granitic gneiss. Pitchblende occurs along veins and fractures. Max RA (SPPY) for the hole is between 534.6 and 534.8 m with 40000+ cps within cataclastic fault planes.
