Using a cut-off of 0.05%; 19.1 m intersected at 1.7% for an overall GT of 33.2; including 3.4 m at 3.0% from 498 to 501.4 m; and 6.4 m at 3.0% from 531.1 to 537.9 m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the 2012 ML SQUID EM pick on L12800E.
HoleGeneralComment: 120 feet of water; put casing in from 42 to 48m; NQ rods broke off at 30m and NW rods fell into the lake. Restarted at a -67 from the same set up.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the 2012 ML SQUID EM pick on L12800E along the Contact conductor. Restart of WC-540.
HoleGeneralComment: Weakly to locally moderately bleached MFc and MFb. Local zones of rubbly core throughout sandstone units associated with quartz dissolution; weakly structured otherwise. Unconformity at 404.5 m. PWP through pelitic gneiss down to 450.1 m. NE/SW trending foliation. Intersected 3 separate graphitic meta-sediment packages. Moderate graphite from 450.1-459.3 m. Followed by two weakly graphitic pelitic gneiss units. Granitic units intermittently distributed throughout basement rock. Slightly structured basement with two weakly sheared zones associated with brittle graphitic fault core. Regional structure from 553 m down to EOH throughout psammo-pelitic garnet-rich gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the 2018 Moving Loop EM pick on L2300 along the Cigar North conductor.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 8.5 m. Strong to moderately bleached sandstone to 200 m; weak to moderate to the Uc. Thin breccias and gouged intervals throughout containing local moderate quartz dissolution. Uc at 561.3 m. Strong red zone paleoweathered pelitic gneiss from UC to 619.2 m. Unusually strong paleoweathering through majority of basement: red and red-green zone alteration extending to 735.3 m. Granitic gneiss and granite from 635.5 m to EOH. Basement lithology is faulted throughout with thin cm-scale gouges, breccias, and common clay replacement. Strongly hematized protocataclasite through coarse-grained and weakly locally foliated granite from 725.6 to 744.4 m. Probing peak of 239 cps in basal MFb conglomerate at 544.1 m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing 20 m south of WC-539 for the down-dip extension of the sandstone structure intersected in the hole. Also testing for an extension of the mineralization encountered at the unconformity and down-dip of the mineralized basement structure. While installing casing the hole veered into the old hole of WC-539; a wedge was set at 31.2 m to start a new hole and achieve the -80 dip; therefore core started at 34 m.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 18.8 m. Sandstone column is dominantly moderately bleached. Grey reduced with local silicification past 400 m. Grey reduced gouge from 467 to 468 m. Uranium mineralization; both bedding and fracture controlled; from 493.9 to the unconformity at 496.9 m. Fracture hosted uranium mineralization in basement between 501.8 and 501.9 m and sporadically between 507.3 and 509.1 m. Overall; structured and altered metasediments to 563.3 m followed by variably altered granitic gneiss to EOH at 644.4 m. Using a cut-off of 0.05%; 8.3 m at 0.5% for an total GT of 4.21; including 5.4 m at 0.7% from 492 to 497.4 m.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting ~90 m north of WC-538; up-dip of the brittle reactivation of the graphitic cataclasite and structure intersected at depth in the hole. Targeted to hit the approximate contact between the graphite package and the footwall granitic gneiss; to test the interpreted main unconformity offsetting fault.
HoleGeneralComment: MFc to 290.6 m with strong bleaching until 188.8 m; weak to locally moderate bleaching to end of interval. MFb from 290.6 - 585.3 m generally weakly bleached with local moderate bleaching in more structured zones. Altered UC 585.3 m. Strong paleoweathering through granitic gneiss to 611.7 m. Cataclastic granitic gneiss from 611.7 - 619.8 m with trace to weak remobilized graphite on fracture planes. Strongly chloritized fine-grained massive granite 619.8 - 623.6 m with rare trace to weak graphite on fractures. Coarse-grained pegmatitic granite 623.6 - 649.1 m with protocataclastic faulting throughout and local brecciation. Moderately to locally strongly chloritized granitic gneiss (649.1 - 711.5 m) with intervals of protocataclastic faulting throughout; moderate to strong remobilized graphite on fractures and in fault gouge. Quartz flooded; brecciated granitic gneiss from 711.5 to end of hole at 713 m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing 30 metres south of WC-523; targeting the main offsetting structure at the unconformity and into the basement - testing for mineralization 300m along strike of WC-539 and 542; down-dip of the significant sandstone structure intersected in WC-523.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 13.4; MFc/Mfb contact 248.8; Uc 490.7 metres. Weak to locally moderate bleaching and moderate silicification past 385 m to the Uc.  Variably graphitic pelitic gneiss with common brittle faulting and ductile shears throughout upper basement from 490.7 to 624.9. Moderate argillization coinciding with weak to moderate chlorite associated with zones of increased structure. Fresh granitic gneiss from 624.9 to the EOH at 650.8 m. Probe peak of 286 cps in the basal sandstone at 475.1 metres.

HolePurposeComment: Targeting the 2018 moving loop EM pick on L1800.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderate to locally strongly bleached upper sandstone to 240 m. Regional mottled purple hematite banding throughout rest of sandstone unit to 282.5 m; moderately bleached 5 m interval directly above the Uc. Poorly structured sandstone overall with local moderate silicification in the basal sandstone. Blocky basal sandstone past 566 m to the Uc at 587.1 m. Large weakly foliated granitic gneiss unit intersected from the Uc down to the end of hole at 711.4 m. Two notable intervals of quartz breccia between 607.9 and 611 m and a larger interval between 633.7 and 654.1 m. Extensive PWP down to 684.7 m with the quartz breccia units being non-paleoweathered. Quite strongly structured throughout basement with two large gouge intervals at 623.8 and 641.4 m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the unconformity ~40 m south of the unconformity of 2017 drill hole WC-519. Testing down-dip of the sandstone structure intersected in the lower sandstone in WC-519 with elevated pathfinders vectoring to the south and potentially along strike of mineralization intersected 400 m to the west in WC-507.
HoleGeneralComment: Largely moderate to strongly bleached MFc with local desilicification associated with fractures in upper MFc. Regional MFb with two intervals of moderate bleaching; grey-reduced alteration; desilicification; and core loss. Common narrow clay gouge intervals in the lower MFb from to 461.8 to 467.2 m and 484 to 494 m. Uc at 497.95 m. Basement consists of trace to weak disseminated graphite pelitic gneiss. Local protocataclastic fabric in the upper basement and an interval of cataclastic to ultracataclastic faulting from 530.4 to 539.15 m. Common anatectic granite between 523.2 and 539.15 m. Pulled for a bit at 560.5 m when rods became stuck just below desilicified interval and hole was lost; however the primary target of the Uc was tested. Probing not complete.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the 2018 EM pick on L3000E between the Cigar North and Tibia drilling areas. Testing for an extension of the cataclasite structures; unconformity offset; and mineralization.
HoleGeneralComment: OB to 56 m. Moderately bleached MFc. Weak to moderately bleached MFb. Generally poorly structured with local intervals of desilicification and increased fracturing. Uc at 492.2 m - sharp at 45 dtca. PWP pelitic gneiss to 503.8 m. Alternating intervals of pelitic gneiss with common feldspar-rich anatectic melt/granitic gneiss throughout. Trace to weak to locally moderate graphite throughout the basement from 522 to the EOH at 647.4 m. Trace to moderate pyrite noted throughout the basement. Basement was poorly structured with local deformation. Protocataclasite from 527-530.6 m. Ductile shear zone from 570.7-583.7 m. Probe peak of 386 cps at 493.2 m in PWP pelitic gneiss.

HolePurposeComment: Testing 45 m south of WC-527; testing down-dip at the unconformity of the sandstone structure; grey reduced alteration; and elevated U partial.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately to strongly bleached MFc sandstone with fracture corridor/protobreccia from 229.7-235.5 m. Weakly bleached MFb with moderate bleaching from 431-521 m; protobreccia interval from 487.2-490.2 m. Uc at 539.7 m - sharp contact. Basement entirely medium to fine-grained anatectic pelitic gneiss. Weakly overprinted PWP to 583.5 m. Trace disseminated graphite beginning at 578.4 m and continuing to end of hole at 611.4 m. Weak to locally moderate chlorite throughout. Relatively competent with semi-frequent fractures throughout; local graphitic fault planes; and rare minor short protobreccia and a narrow graphitic clay gouge at 610.95 m.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the 2004 EM pick on L2200E. Testing for an extension of the cataclasite structures; unconformity offset; and mineralization on the easternmost portion of the Cigar North conductor towards the Tibia Lake trend.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately bleached throughout with a few intervals throughout the MFb of weak bleaching. Several larger rubbly/blocky fracture corridors through the MFb with desilicification. Lower structure interval from 491.7 to 500 m with abundant clay gouge; breccia (incohesive and cohesive); and remobilized hematite. Grey-reduced alteration in basal sandstone. Intact Uc at 504.9 m. Weakly graphitic pelitic gneiss with local cataclastic fabric to 531.9 m; large cataclastic fault zone from 531.9 to 550.8 m; and footwall granite from 550.8 m to the EOH at 608.4 m. Trace Umin intersected in the upper basement in bleached competent pelitic gneiss locally between 507.6 and 509.3 m. Using a cut-off of 0.05% eU; WC-549 intersected 2.4 m at 0.25% eU for a total GT of 0.6; including 2.2 m at 0.26% eU.

HolePurposeComment: Testing the up-dip expression of the main off-setting graphitic cataclastic fault between hanging wall metasediments and footwall granitic gneiss and weak uranium mineralization intersected in WC-549; analogous to faulting observed further east along strike on the Cigar North trend.
HoleGeneralComment: Moderately to strongly bleached MFc and largely moderately to strongly bleached MFb sandstone with a few intervals of moderate diagenetic hematite. Competent MFc sandstone. Moderate to strongly structured MFb below 320 m with fracturing breccia and clay gouge. Potential fanglomerate/breccia in basal sandstone from 484.5 m to a faulted Uc at 487.6 m. Basement consists of altered/structured (gouge breccia early cataclasite) metasedimentary gneiss from Uc to 496 m. Main graphitic cataclastic fault zone from 496 to 502.6 m and footwall granite with weak to moderate argillization and weak muddy green alteration from 502.6 m to end of hole at 533.4 m. Moderate argillization/brittle reactivation/breccia throughout much of upper basement with associated hydrothermal hematite and limonite. Trace Umin intersected sporadically between 495.5 and 500.8 m associated with breccia and argillized cataclasite with radiometric peak of 1150 cps from 495.9 to 496 m.
